title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, spread in shallow baking dish.
Cover with broken potato chips.
Bake uncovered for 1/2 to 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: apple coconut cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Set aside. Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes. Add flour mixture. Mix at low speed just until blended. Fold in pecans, apples and coconut. (Batter will be stiff.) Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool cake about 30 minutes. Remove from pan and immediately drizzle glaze over cake. Yield: one 10-inch cake. Will serve about 20, as it is quite rich.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients for meatballs and form into balls.
Brown and place in 9 x 13-inch
casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Shake milk and flour in jar to get out lumps.
Add cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt margarine, then add sugar, eggs, flour and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon until done.
Leave grease in pot.
Then add tomato sauce, onion, bell pepper, sausage, bacon, salt, black pepper, sugar and rice altogether.
Cook on medium heat for 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: caramel custard
directions: In a heavy pan over low heat, cook and stir 3/4 cup sugar until melted and golden.
Pour into eight 6 ounce custard cups. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons of flour and baking soda.
Cream shortening. Add sugar and eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add flour, spices, baking powder, soda and sour milk.
Mix well and add prunes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Blend yogurt and whipped topping with a spoon, not blender. Pour into pie crust and garnish with fruit or sprinkles.
Chill 2 hours or longer.
Pie may be frozen.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Flour pork chops well. Brown in hot shortening. Put in crock-pot.
Add 1 tablespoon Italian dressing for each pork chop. Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours or in microwave for 5 minutes. (Kansas.)

title: clams chesapeake
directions: Mix all ingredients above together.
Top clams or oysters on 1/2 shell with mixture topped with a slice of raw bacon.
Bake on rock salt for about 10 to 15 minutes, until bacon is crisp.
Makes approximately 2 dozen (depending on size).

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in large ovenproof bowl and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and honey.
Blend well. Add lemon juice, nuts and pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream. Freeze.

title: chicken almond salad
directions: Combine first
ingredients.
Cut the tomatoes into 6 wedges, but not all
the way through.
Spread wedges apart and sprinkle insides with small amount of salt.
Place each tomato on lettuce leaves
and spoon in the chicken mixture.
Sprinkle top with crumbled
bacon
and
almonds.
Cover and chill well. Serve with your favorite crackers.
Serves 2.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and let congeal.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust.
Chill several hours. Easy as pie to make.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In top	of
double
boiler
put
sugar, salt, cocoa and flour. Add
milk	and
egg
yolks.
Cook over hot water until thick. Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool and put in pie shell (baked). Whip
egg
whites by hand until stiff.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Put	on top of pie.	Bake until browned at 350°.

title: chocolate macaroon brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Crumble together.
Press into regular sized buttered cake pan.

title: italian green noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef, turkey or chicken.
Drain and set aside.

title: cinnamon pull-a-way
directions: Let frozen rolls rise for 1 hour.
Dip each roll into melted oleo, then into mixture of butterscotch pudding, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Place in buttered Bundt pan and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: lemon sauce for bread pudding
directions: Boil together water, sugar and cornstarch.
Remove from fire. Add lemon juice and butter and cook until clear.
Add lemon peel if wanted.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into pieces (as for potato salad).
Mix potatoes and cheese in casserole.
Cut margarine into pieces and place over potatoes.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Salt to taste. Cover and cook in microwave until potatoes are tender (approximately 10 minutes).

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef; drain fat and stir in macaroni, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook until macaroni is transparent.
Add sauce, water, Worcestershire and sugar.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Pour 1/2 in casserole dish, then put 1/2 cup cheese, then pour in the rest and top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook at 350° to melt cheese.

title: brown sugar pound cake(won first place blue ribbon state fair 1992)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat butter and shortening together. Gradually add the sugars, creaming until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk and vanilla to the creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts (if used).
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done when tested with a straw or cake tester.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from the pan.
Pour glaze over hot cake.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water.
Drain.
Mix broccoli, soup, mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix well.
Add onion and eggs.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with shredded cheese and crumble Townhouse crackers on top.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes. Top will be brown.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, sour cream, milk, butter and corn syrup in a heavy 2 quart pan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar dissolves and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil to soft ball, 238 degrees.
Allow to stand to 110 degrees about an hour.
Add vanilla and beat until it begins to lose its gloss (requires little beating).
Quickly stir in nuts and turn into oiled pan.
Let stand until firm, cut.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put the butter in a large bowl. Add the sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
When cold, roll out on floured surface and cut into desired shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool on wire rack. Frost with any frosting.
Decorate, if desired.

title: veal and peppers italiano
directions: Trim separable fat from veal.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Spray a cold large skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Brown veal in the hot skillet.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, water, sliced leek or green onion, garlic, basil, chicken bouillon granules, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add green peppers.
Cook, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Stir together 2 tablespoons water and cornstarch.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Serve with hot, cooked noodles.
Yield:
4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: "hot dog" kraut
directions: Combine all ingredients. Keep in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: cindie's alaskan oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook peanut butter, vanilla, cocoa, sugar and butter over medium heat until fudge-like consistency.
Pour in oatmeal.
Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add egg, oil and milk. Have skillet hot and add small amount of oil. Put small amounts of pancake batter in hot pan and cook on one side until brown. Turn and brown on other side.

title: freezer sandwiches
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oleo until soft, but not brown. Add sugar, mustard and ketchup.
Add chipped ham.
Stir well. Place on 1/2 bun.
Add a slice of cheese and top with other 1/2 bun.
Wrap in tinfoil and freeze until ready to use.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; cool and grate them.
Heat 1/2 cup butter with soup, blend in sour cream, onions and cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with cornflake crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party fruit punch(a superb wedding punch!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except ginger ale or Sprite) in a very large container.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
(Sugar may be omitted if you feel that some you will be serving are diabetic!) Pour into 5 to 6 five quart plastic buckets.
(Ice cream buckets are excellent for freezing.)
Put in freezer.
Serves 150 to 200.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender. Drain. Put into casserole dish and mash with fork. Add chicken soup, mushroom soup, sour cream and cheese. Mix well. Sprinkle corn bread stuffing over top and add pats of butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bird nests
directions: In saucepan, combine corn syrup, brown sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir constantly until mixture boils.
Pour hot mixture over Rice Krispies and coconut.
Blend.
Shape into firm balls the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and make indentation to form a nest.
Fill with M&M's, jelly beans, etc.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease, line and flour a tube pan. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten eggs, oil and pumpkin. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick entered in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing to cake platter.
Frost with cream cheese icing and sprinkle chopped pecans or walnuts over all.

title: chicken fried in batter
directions: Wash chicken, cook until partially tender, simmering in boiling water 30 minutes or longer, depending on size.
Drain, cool,
sprinkle with salt,
pepper,
celery
salt
or
poultry seasoning.
Beat eggs, add
milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat into milk mixture, blend in shortening. If batter becomes thick upon
standing,
thin
with
or
2 tablespoons milk.
Dip pieces of chicken into batter, allowing to drip slightly.
Fry
in
preheated shortening at 375° until golden brown.
(Slip
pieces
carefully
into hot shortening). Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve piping hot.
Fry time about 5 to 7 minutes.
Save broth for soup.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil in saucepan.
Heat just until sugar melts, or is liquid looking.
Set aside to cool. Pour sauerkraut into large bowl; add chopped celery, red onion and bell pepper. Pour cooled liquid over salad mixture.
Let stand 24 hours, stirring several times.
Very good with meat.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place ingredients in a glass dish and bake one hour at 350°.

title: basil buttered beans
directions: In a saucepan, combine beans, onion, celery and water.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until tender; drain.
Add the butter, basil, salt and pepper.
Stir to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 1 hour.

title: squash and carrot casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except oleo and croutons.
Place half the mixture in greased casserole.
Add squash mixture and place remaining croutons on top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add the egg and beat.
Add the vanilla, almond flavoring, flour, salt and baking soda; mix.
Add the walnuts and mix well.
Shape into a roll; refrigerate.
Slice off thin pieces, about 1/4-inch.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 3 dozen.
They freeze very well as dough or as cookie.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Soften gelatin with hot water; add cold water.	Add mayo and onion juice; add tuna and celery; add peas and chopped onion. Pour into casserole dish and let congeal overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine and add peanut butter; blend well.
Mix crumbs, coconut, peanuts and sugar.
Add to margarine mixture and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Let melt to smooth consistency.
Dip balls in chocolate and let cool on wax paper.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush graham crackers. Measure 1 1/2 cups and press gently into pan with melted butter. Mix chocolate chips, chopped walnuts and coconut in a bowl.
Place on top of crushed grahams and butter.
Add one can of sweetened condensed milk on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Cut into desired size squares.

title: heavenly potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes for 20 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Peel potatoes and grate into 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: world's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine white and brown sugars.
Add butter and cream together with the sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, mixing well.
In a separate bowl, sift the flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture; mix well.
The dough will be stiff.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Using a small ice cream scoop, drop dough onto the cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool on wire racks.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.

title: no crust green chili quiche
directions: Chop chilies and spread in a greased 8 x 11 pan.
Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs, half and half and worcestershire; pour over cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes (till firm and light brown on top).

title: strawberry salad
directions: First, mix all together.
It's so easy.
Pour into casserole dish.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8.

title: baked turkey salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except potato chips and almonds. Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips and top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle toasted, slivered almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash the cooked yams while hot.
Stir in the butter, honey and beaten egg
yolks.
Beat the mixture until fluffy.
Mix the orange juice or milk with the brown sugar, nutmeg, mace and salt.
Add it slowly to the yam mixture, beating constantly.

Beat the egg whites until very stiff and fold them gently into yam mixture. Pour into buttered casserole and bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown and well puffed.

title: fresh apple cake(baking time: 1 hour)
directions: Peel apples and chop.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Gently add apples.
Flour nuts lightly and add to cake mixture.
Grease 10-inch tube pan and line bottom with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Glaze while warm.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Mix Soy Sauce, ground ginger and sugar.
Place drained chestnuts in mixture for 30 minutes.
Remove and wrap with bacon and bake at 375° until bacon is done.
Secure with toothpick.

title: almond punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale immediately before serving. Serves about 30.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: agnes' macaroni salad
directions: Stir lemon juice into milk until milk thickens; add salad dressing,
black pepper, and mustard and mix well.
Combine salad dressing
mixture with remaining ingredients; toss lightly until well mixed.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: terrific cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except for nuts.
Roll into ball form. Chill 5 hours then roll in nuts to cover.
To freeze wrap in plastic wrap then in aluminum foil.

title: broccoli and cheese tortellini
directions: Chop fresh broccoli and steam until tender; set aside.
Cook tortellini according to directions in bag.
Set aside.
Combine in large frying pan the butter, oleo and garlic cloves.
Simmer on low until garlic is tender.
Add to broccoli and tortellini.
Cook until hot.

title: chicken with balsamic vinegar
directions: Coat large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken 5 to 8 minutes over medium-high heat; remove to plate and keep warm.
Recoat skillet with cooking spray. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cook peppers, mushrooms, onion and garlic until peppers are crisp-tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Whisk together hot pepper sauce, vinegar and sugar.
Add to skillet and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add chicken; cover and simmer, turning occasionally, until chicken is tender, about 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: tropical popcorn
directions: Mix all together. Store in airtight container. Makes 12 cups.

title: cream turkey over rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a skillet and heat until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: With wire whisk, mix egg, basil, salt, pepper and water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Grease shallow pan with butter.
Place chicken in pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: skillet zucchini
directions: Cook celery and onion in oil until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes or until zucchini is tender-crisp.

title: fruit cocktail dessert cake
directions: Mix all these ingredients, except fruit.
Add 1 cup fruit cocktail.
Pour into a 9-inch pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in quiche dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until light golden brown on top.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch pie plate about 3/4 full with sliced apples. Sprinkle one tablespoon of sugar and one teaspoon of cinnamon over the apples.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add nuts.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
Make small marble sized balls.
Bake on ungreased pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together and put into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May be glazed with 1/2 cup lemon juice and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 12 x 16-inch pan, dump cans of pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Spread and mix to cover bottom of pan.
Dump box of dry cake mix on top and spread evenly.
Put the margarine on top, spacing evenly.
Bake 1 hour or until top is brown.
Serve hot.

title: nanny's beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
While beans are cooking, add all other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until tender.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet with rolls.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread mixture onto rolled out rolls (cooled).
Add vegetables, making layers as you go, starting with broccoli and ending with shredded cheese.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients, then chips.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Let cool slightly on cookie sheet before removing.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in greased square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a small saucepan, mix brown sugar, flour and milk over low flame until mixture thickens slightly.
Put over cake at serving time.

title: knox blocks
directions: Make gelatine.
Pour into pan and let set.
Cut into blocks. Kids especially like this in the summertime.
It makes no mess.

title: hershey's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients and pur into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions in skillet.
Add Chili-O mix and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook yellow rice as directed. Beginning with rice, layer in a casserole dish.
There will be 2 layers each.
Mix Cheddar cheese soup and milk.
Heat and pour over the top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in salted water.
Drain.
Melt cheese and butter together and add to spinach.
Put in casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese and pecans.
Heat at 350°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9x13-inch baking pan. In a medium bowl, beat together butter, brown sugar and eggs until light.
Add flour, soda, honey and milk all at once.
Beat just until smooth.
In a medium bowl, toss together figs, raisins, almonds and spices.
Fold into the cake batter and pour into prepared pan.
Bake until center springs back when gently touched. About 45 to 50 minutes.

title: janice's chocolate trifle
directions: *Instead of Kahlua you may substitute a mixture of 1 teaspoon sugar and 4 tablespoons of leftover black coffee.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; add buttermilk and beaten egg; beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chunky apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Peel and dice apple. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain the pineapple just a bit.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.
Sets up in the refrigerate almost immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in order. Cover top with bread crumbs. Cover top of bread crumbs with 1 stick of butter, sliced.

title: fresh apple bundt cake
directions: Combine apples, sugar, and nuts.
Let stand an hour, stirring frequently.
Mix oil, eggs, and vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients. Stir in apple mixture by hand until well blended.
Place in a well-greased (but not floured) bundt pan.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Beat egg in small bowl with fork.
Dip each chicken breast in egg, then coat in bread crumbs.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Cook chicken breast over medium heat until browned on both sides.
May need additional butter.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable spray.
Place drained noodles in dish, top with chicken.
Pour Prego sauce over top of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; top with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer until cheese is melted.

title: orange molded salad
directions: Bring pineapple and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in pecans.
Fold in whipped topping and buttermilk.
Pour in an 8-cup mold.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: raindrop raspberry tea
directions: In a saucepan bring the water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover and steep for 5 minutes.
Discard bags. Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add cold water and juice concentrate; mix well.
Serve over ice.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: sauerkraut with lima beans or peas
directions: Wash sauerkraut well.
Place in a 2-quart pot and add enough water to just cover . Cook slowly 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Saute onion in oil until soft and light yellow. Sprinkle flour over the onions and brown very lightly.
Add some of the liquid from the cooked sauerkraut to onions; season.
Add garlic; stir constantly until sauce thickens.
Add lima beans or peas to sauerkraut.
Then add sauce to sauerkraut and stir to mix well.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Bring to boil 1/4 cup Karo, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/8 cup margarine. Let boil 1 minute. Add Rice Krispies; mix well. Press Rice Krispies in 13 x 9 pan. Place in freezer.

title: crisp coated fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in milk and drain.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Place one piece of chicken at a time in bag and shake to coat evenly with flour.
Fry chicken in hot oil, about 1 1/2 inches deep, until brown and crisp on both sides, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash and pat chicken pieces with flour.
Cook in hot oil for 15 to 20 minutes; set chicken aside.
Add all of the remaining ingredients; cook for 10 minutes.
Add chicken; cook for 50 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: meat and potato pie(idaho style)
directions: Melt Crisco in 4-quart saucepan.
Add steak.
Brown on medium high heat.
Add onions and carrots.
Cook until onions begin to brown.
Stir often.
Add tomato paste, basil, thyme and garlic powder.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes stirring constantly.
Add broth and potatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are just done but firm.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in green peas.
Cool to room temperature.
Heat oven to 375°. Spoon filling into unbaked pie shell.
Moisten pastry edge with water.
Roll top crust same as bottom.
Trim excess, flute and prick crust with fork to make slits.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until browned.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 10 minutes; cool.

title: baked cream cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage (course) and cook 9 minutes in boiling salt water.
Remove cabbage.
Drain well.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart dish.
Melt butter; stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk gradually.
Continue stirring until it thickens.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or crumbs are brown.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Steam cauliflower and broccoli until tender.
Melt cheese into a cheese sauce by adding milk and cooking over low heat.
Combine cooked rice, broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms and water chestnuts into large casserole.
Add the 2 cans of soup and stir.
If the mixture is too thick, add milk to moisten it.
Pour cheese sauce over entire dish.
Bake covered for about 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: sirloin steak
directions: Cut all fat from steak.
Season on both sides.
Place into hot oil and brown on both sides.
Cook until well done.

title: bacon in batter
directions: Fry bacon, cut in fairly thick slices, until brown but not crisp. Drain from fat, leaving a little fat in the pan. Pick each bacon strip up with a fork. Dip into batter made of other ingredients; fry in fat until brown.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil sugar and 5 cups water; let cool.
Boil 2 cups water and tea bags; let cool.
Add frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade and brandy.
Freeze.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter with pastry blender until crumbly; save 1 cup for topping.
Add rest of ingredients.
Keep reserved crumbs; mix the rest.
It will be runny and thin.
Pour into greased pans; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until it tests done with toothpick.
The cake will stay in the pan; it sticks.
Cut into sections and it can be gotten out nicely.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine rest of milk, cake mix and melted margarine; mix.
Press 1/2 of mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Top with caramel mixture (spreading to edges).
Top with teaspoonful of remaining cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: orange peel bread
directions: Peel outer skins of oranges with vegetable peeler to fill one cup easily.
Chop into small pieces and put in small pan with enough water to cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Add 1 cup sugar and boil 10 minutes until syrupy.
Cream butter with 1/2 cup sugar; add egg and milk.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt and add to butter, beating well.
Add orange peel syrup.
Divide batter between two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch greased bread pans.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and potatoes (mash potatoes).
Stir in rest of ingredients and simmer until done.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple on top. Sprinkle cake mix over the mixture and dot with butter.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be served with whip cream.

title: creole shrimp soup
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until shrimp are tender and rice is cooked, about 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked apples(with equal)
directions: Pare apples halfway and core.
Place in microwave dish.
Place 1 teaspoon butter and 1 package Equal in each core.
Dust top with cinnamon.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High approximately 7 minutes.
Time will depend on the type of apples used.

title: fried pinto bean patties
directions: Mash beans; add egg, salt and pepper to taste and a small amount of flour to make it stick together.
Add a pinch of baking powder to the flour.
Make into patties and fry in hot oil.
Bits of onion may be added to the beans.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash orange, apples and cranberries.
Put all ingredients in food chopper (except sugar) on medium.
Remove and add the sugar, mixing well.
Chill.

title: kentucky easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water. Add sugar, oil, egg and flour.
Mix until well blended.
Cover and place in refrigerator and let rise overnight.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Wrap each chicken breast with dried beef, then wrap with slice of bacon.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked zucchini with tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Trim zucchini and core the tomatoes.
Cut each into equal horizontal slices.
Arrange in ovenproof baking dish with the edges slightly overlapping, alternating layers of zucchini and tomatoes.
Put green pepper, onions, garlic, marjoram and pepper to taste in mixing bowl.
Blend well and scatter over zucchini and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with the olive oil and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: arizona mountain soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In large kettle, combine beans and 3 cups water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour or cover and let stand overnight.
Drain.

title: biscuit sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Drain.
In bowl, combine eggs, cheese and sausage mixture.
Separate dough into 8 biscuits; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter over biscuits.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in preheated oven until quiche is set and crust is golden brown. Serves 8.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and onion.
Add hash browns and cheese and mix well.
Cover with Corn Flakes.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 425°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: peach fizz
directions: Place peaches in blender.
Add pineapple and lemon or lime juice; blend until peaches are broken up.
Add ice and blend until thick.
Add ginger ale and blend.
Serve with peach slice.
Makes 6 (8 ounce) servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and fresh mushrooms in butter until slightly soft.
Add tuna, mushroom soup and enough milk to make thick and creamy.
Boil noodles to desired tenderness.
Mix tuna mixture with drained noodles and place in buttered casserole dish. Top with crushed potato chips or sliced cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cranberry-pear relish
directions: Combine sugar plus 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil; dissolve sugar.
Boil rapidly, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add additional ingredients.
Cook until cranberries pop (3 to 4 minutes).
Cover and chill.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute bacon and onions. Add flour (make a roux). Slowly add bouillon cubes. Add potatoes. Simmer 1 hour. Beat eggs. Add sour cream to eggs. Add 1 cup hot soup mixture to egg mixture. Blend well and return to soup.

title: sausage skillet supper
directions: Brown sausage in buttered frypan.
Add rice, soup and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in frozen peas and mushrooms.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: In 10-cup ring mold, add each mixture separately and refrigerate the following:

title: scallop kabobs italian-style
directions: Wrap each scallop with a strip of ham; thread 6 scallops onto each of 6 (12-inch) skewers.
Set aside.
Coat a small nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot. Add garlic; saute until browned.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, parsley and oregano.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place kabobs on rack and cook 9 minutes, turning and basting frequently with lemon juice mixture.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows and dissolve.
Stir into popcorn.
Add candy and peanuts.
Form into balls or place in a well-greased tube pan.

title: fresh vegetable medley
directions: About 15 minutes before serving, bring to boil water and 1/2 teaspoon of table salt in large saucepan.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 5 to 8 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp. Drain well.
Spoon into serving dish.
Stir in remaining table salt and butter.
Makes 8 servings.

title: krispie cookies
directions: Combine
sugar	and
butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in Rice Krispies, semi-sweet chocolate chips and raisins (optional).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: nine-day slaw
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and blend well.
Then combine the oil, vinegar, salt and sugar; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over cabbage mixture immediately.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cover chicken breasts, celery and onion with water and cook until tender.
Remove chicken and dice.
Add rice, soups and diced chicken to water; simmer until rice is done.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and crumbled crackers to taste.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and browns on top.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 2 c. flour, butter, and confectioners sugar well.
Work with hands, kneading it until it is a good consistency dough. Transfer to a baking dish.
Using the palm of your hand, pat down evenly until you have one uniform layer in the bottom of the pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Beat eggs well and mix in lemon juice.
Add all other ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Spread this evenly over the first layer and return to 350 degree oven for another 25 minutes or until the second layer is firm.
It must not be runny at all.
Remove from oven and cool. Sprinkle top lightly with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: italian herbed potatoes
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, stir green onions, butter, parsley flakes, Italian seasoning and salt together.
Microwave, covered, on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until onions are tender.
Stir in potatoes.
Cook, covered, on High for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese, tossing to coat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, then add cold water.
Allow to nearly set.

title: lemon rice
directions: Combine rice, margarine, garlic, lemon peel, pepper and broth in a 2 to 3-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil. Stir once or twice. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Stir in parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Lightly brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Stir in 3 cups medium egg noodles, cooked and drained.
Pour into 3-quart casserole pan. Mix 2 cups bread cubes in 1 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: crock-pot candy
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot in order listed. Do not stir. Cook on low heat for 2 hours. Stir well and drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls. Let cool. Put in airtight container.

title: sees fudge
directions: Process in a blender the sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Melt the butter and chocolate chips together.
Add the nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: marinated texas shrimp(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Thaw shrimp, if necessary.
Peel and devein.
Cook in boiling water until pink.
Do not overcook.
Drain.

title: smoked salmon tarts
directions: Cut each pie crust into 14 circles, using a 2 1/2-inch cutter. Place rounds in greased miniature muffin cups.
Trim excess pastry.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to cream mixture, alternately with milk, beat well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: date and nut squares
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Mix nuts and dates and mix with flour, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Add the four eggs, that have been beaten for one minute.
Fold into the mixture.
Butter an 8 x 14-inch pan thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from pan and invert on a rack.
Put confectioners sugar on all sides of each square.
(Cut into squares when cool before sprinkling with sugar.)

title: baked vegetable casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add another cup grated Swiss cheese on top and bake, uncovered, for another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, melt butter in oven; remove.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add flour, milk and seasonings.
Mix well and add cheese, spinach and onion.
Pour into baking dish and bake 35 minutes. Cool for 45 minutes, cut into bite-size pieces

title: apres ski penne rustica(yield:  6-8 servings)
directions: 1. Boil pasta.
Drain and set aside.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Brown hamburger, garlic, green pepper and onion in margarine; drain. Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar. Make a mixture of cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese. In 9 x 12-inch pan, layer noodles, cheese, cheese mixture and hamburger sauce. Repeat and top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Can freeze.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add milk and lemon rind. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in bread loaf pan.
Prepare juice from 1 lemon with 1/4 cup sugar. Allow to dissolve.
Pour over hot bread and let it soak in.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and place in baking dish.
Top with corn flakes or bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: square meal snack
directions: Saute peppers, onions and mushrooms in butter and olive oil. Add cumin, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine mustard, mayonnaise and horseradish and spread on toasted bread.
Place bread on 4 Corning snack dishes and spread with pepper mixture.
Add beef or ham, then tomato slice.
Top with grated cheese.
Place under broiler until bubbly and brown.
Serves 4.

title: gumbo, country style
directions: Blend flour in oil in Dutch oven or large pot (preferably cast-iron).
Cook, stirring constantly, until flour turns a deep brown.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in broth, tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Cook okra just until it begins to brown.
Add chicken, shrimp and okra.
Cover and cook for another 30 minutes.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Stir in file before serving.
Do not boil once file is added.

title: rocky roads
directions: Mix egg and confectioners sugar together.
Add marshmallows. Melt in double boiler or in microwave the morsels and margarine. Combine with above mixture.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan, buttered and sprinkled with coconut.
Put coconut on top.

title: old witches nut cake
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin, oil and water together.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into 2 floured loaf pans approximately 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until toothpick comes clean.
Cool.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine in a large glass bowl.
Cook 4 minutes, then stir well.
Cook additional 3 to 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter, cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from
heat.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently and pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break.
This mixture is extremely hot so be careful.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beaten egg whites.
When mixed, fold in egg whites.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato-apple casserole(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange apples and yams in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in alternating layers.
In a saucepan, bring syrup and cider to a boil; remove from heat and pour over yams and apples. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover baking dish with foil; bake one hour.
Uncover; bake until yams are soft and syrup is thick, about 15 or 20 minutes more.

title: date cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine dates and boiling water; cool to room temperature.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In a large mixer bowl, beat shortening about 30 seconds. Add sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Add dry ingredients and cooled undrained date mixture alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
If desired, serve each piece with a dollop of whipped cream.
Serves 12.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken, skin and take off bone.
Save liquid and set chicken aside.
Add to the liquid, the onion, celery, salt, pepper, corn, limas, tomatoes, potatoes, catsup and vinegar.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle topping over pineapple and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cook all together.
Cool and put in baked pie shell.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Just mix in a 13 x 9-inch dish and put chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: aunt minnie's pancakes
directions: Mix milk, egg and oleo.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Yield:

title: date-nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let set.
Cream together butter, eggs and sugar.
Add date mixture and flour and nut meats. Bake in 2 loaf pans in moderate oven for about 45 minutes or until it falls away from the pan.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Sift and then add rest of ingredients to pumpkin mixture.
Spoon batter into 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan.
Bake 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy artichoke heart appetizers
directions: Unroll dough into rectangles.
Press onto bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with thin red pepper slices.

title: frosty lemon cooler
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle 3/4 of the crumbs in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir together egg yolk, lemon peel and juice.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.

title: butterscotch nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light, add brown sugar and continue beating until light with rotary beater or mixer.
Add vanilla and melted butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk.
Add chopped nuts with the last addition of flour.
Pour into 2 9 X 5 inch loaf pans, greased lightly and floured.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken up.
Grease pan.
Mix chicken and 2 cans of soup together and spread in pan.
Mix milk, flour and melted butter together and pour over chicken and soup mixture.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pretzel strawberry
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar together and remove from heat. Blend in pretzels and spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch glass pan. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Cool and set aside.
Mix together strawberry jello and boiling water until all granules are dissolved and then add cold water and strawberries. Let thicken slightly in refrigerator.
Set aside.
Whip together whipped topping, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Top with strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate and let firm before serving.

title: chicken breast with dressing
directions: In a well-greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish or pan, layer cooked and shredded chicken in pan.
Mix both cans of soup and milk in bowl; pour over chicken in pan.
Sprinkle stuffing over mixture in pan.
Take the reserved broth and pour 1 1/2 to 2 cups broth over mixture in pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar, crackers and soda.
Add butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add coconut and vanilla; stir to blend.
Press half of mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover with pie filling and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: midnight bliss cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour bundt cake pan.

title: grandma hendricks chocolate cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Pour enough hot boiling water into the cocoa to make a thin paste; fill cup with sweet milk.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with cocoa liquid, to wet mixture.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Bake in greased square cake pan at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until done.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini as desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dip zucchini in an Egg Batter, then roll in flour and fry in hot oil.

title: home chili
directions: Prepare meat. Add canned vegetables, drained if pasta prepared separately. Add paste and onion; heat to simmer.

Add spices and simmer for 1/2 hour. (If pasta added before it is cooked, add with spices and simmer until pasta is soft, then cover and cook on low for another 1/2 hour.) Add prepared pasta and cook on low 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken curry
directions: Melt butter and brown curry powder in it. Add onion, mushrooms, celery and apple to curried butter; mix thoroughly. Add beef broth and bring to just a boil.
Add lite cream and milk. Return to a boil.
Mix cornstarch and water; add to sauce until thickened. Salt to taste.
Add diced, cooked chicken and heat. Serve over hot rice with condiments (raisins, sauteed onions, nuts, chutney, coconut, etc.).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chilies rellenos con queso(green chilies stuffed with cheese)
directions: Cut
cheese
in
rectangles
about
1/2-inch
thick and 1-inch long.
Cut	chilies
into
2 strips and wrap around the cheese, securing with a toothpick or I leave the chilies whole and stuff the
cheese, cut at an angle, down into the chilies. This is easier
and
less time consuming.
Lay in a casserole dish and cover with sauce.

title: coffee cake cookies
directions: Scald milk and cool.
Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine eggs with milk. Add yeast and liquids to flour mixture.
Mix lightly until flour is moist.
Do not knead.
Divide the dough in 1/3; roll out like cinnamon rolls.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on rolled out dough. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: venison sausage patties
directions: Grind the venison with the bacon. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix well and form into patties. Cook until well done.

title: quick barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in covered dish at 400° about an hour.

title: cod or haddock italian style
directions: Cut fish into 3 servings.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place in a glass oven dish.
Pour tomato sauce and lemon juice over fish. Sprinkle with cheese and dot with butter or oleo.
Bake in a hot 400° oven until fish has browned lightly and fish flakes, about 25 minutes.

title: raspberry glazed wings
directions: In saucepan, combine jam, vinegar, soy sauce, garlic and 1 teaspoon black pepper.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Cut chicken wings into three sections; discard wing tips.
Place wings in a large bowl; add raspberry mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.
Line a 10 x 15-inch baking pan with foil and grease the foil.
Using a slotted spoon and reserving the marinade, place wings in pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes, turning once.
Cook reserved marinade for 10 minutes; brush over wings and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix meal, 2 tablespoons of flour, 2 eggs, 1/2 cup of milk and 3 tablespoons of oil.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake until brown.

title: whacky cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Add vinegar, oil and vanilla. Lastly, add the water.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 5 x 7-inch glass dish.
Top with 1/2 cup chopped pecans, sauteed in 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: yogurt pie
directions: In a large bowl, microwave cream cheese on High about 1 minute to soften.
Stir in yogurt and brown sugar.
Blend until smooth. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Pour into pie crust.
Microwave on 50% power for 5 minutes.
Chill and garnish with chopped nuts or fresh fruit.
Makes a 9 inch pie.

title: ramen noodle soup
directions: Brown pork in hot oil in large saucepan.
Add 1 seasoning packet and remaining ingredients, except garnish.
Cook 3 minutes. Garnish with tortilla strips and green onions. Serve immediately.

title: greatmaw's salad
directions: Wash and tear lettuce in small pieces.
Add boiled eggs, sugar and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: jeannette's easy chicken casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread undiluted soup on top of chicken.
Place prepared stuffing on top of chicken soup.
Pour milk over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Mix and pour into greased cake pan and bake at 350° until almost set.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange; cover with sugar and set aside. Put water on jello and mix; set aside.
Now mix all the ingredients together.
Put in a mold and refrigerate.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Brown bacon (and sausage if using it) in a large frying pan with onion.
Remove meat from pan.
Add hash browns and green pepper.
Cook until brown.
Return meat to pan.
Add eggs, cream cheese, grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn frequently.
Cook until eggs are set.
Serves 8.

title: easy no bake lemon pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all ingredients and pour into crust. Chill for one hour.
Serve.

title: penne super casserole
directions: Cook penne in boiling, salted water, following package directions and drain.
Heat oil in a large saucepot.
Add onions and garlic and saute
at low heat.
Stir in tomatoes plus 1 can liquid.
Break up tomatoes.
Stir in paste, sugar and salt.

title: dessert or salad
directions: Beat egg whites; add baking powder, sugar, nuts (if desired) and Ritz crackers (crumbled coarsely).
Spread in butter lined long pan, then add egg mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread on rolls.
Chop fine and mix together 3/4 cup each of the following: green onions, cauliflower, carrots, green pepper, broccoli, celery, mushrooms, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Spread on top of the cream cheese mixture and press firmly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar over finely chopped apples. Stir in remaining ingredients until blended. Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: holiday mulled wine
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil. Serve warm.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Scoop out inside, being careful not to break shell.
Cook pulp well in a small amount of salted water.
Mash and season with black pepper to taste.
Add cracker crumbs, cream and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into shells and sprinkle with grated onion, then grated cheese and paprika. Place in shallow pan with about 1/4-inch water.
Bake thirty minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine vanilla wafers and butter until moist.
Press into the bottom of the container.
Mix well cream cheese, beaten egg and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of crust.
Slice bananas on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add crushed pineapple to top of bananas. Cover with Cool Whip.
(May sprinkle top of Cool Whip with chopped pecans and dot with cherries!)
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage and beans
directions: Quarter, core and chop the savoy cabbage.
Steam in 4 to 5 cups of water until tender, then drain in colander and set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in a greased baking dish.
Bake one hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; beat on slow speed.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour.
Add rolled oats and coconut until well blended.
Last, add Rice Krispies.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
(I use a No. 45 scoop, which is about 2 tablespoons.)

title: punch
directions: Mix and pour over softened sherbet. When mixed, pour on 2-quarts of ginger ale.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the almonds, potato chips and cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the almonds, potato chips and cheese on top and bake in the oven at 450° for 20 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: orange jello salad
directions: In a bowl, mix Jell-O with boiling water until dissolved.
Add in oranges, orange juice and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until set.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Add Cool Whip and stir until smooth.
Pour over the top of set Jell-O.
Sprinkle cheese and nuts on top.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Grease large skillet lightly with fat from meat.
Brown meat thoroughly and season with salt.
Push meat to one section.
Add onions.
Cook and stir until tender.
Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add green peppers.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well.
Save some noodles to go on top.
Bake in greased casserole 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lela's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, cheese, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Mix well. Scour pan with steel wool.
Rinse and dry.
Spray with Pam.
Start in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into large meatballs.
Place into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Soak chicken in oil for at least 1/2 hour before cooking; drain well.
Mix spices together.
Grill chicken 15 to 20 minutes on both sides.
Turn and baste with lemon butter sauce; sprinkle with spices.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Turn, baste and sprinkle.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Turn, baste and sprinkle.
Cook for 10 minutes. Entire cooking time should be from 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 20 minutes, depending on how well done you want it.
This is done on a Weber or covered barbecue.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over bran, raisins and dates and set aside. Mix other ingredients except nuts in mixer.
Stir in bran mixture and nuts.
Bake in well-oiled muffin tins 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Let cool in tins 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Stir in corn.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until done (approximately 45 minutes).
Corn will be fluffy and brown on top when done.

title: cooled strawberry fluff
directions: Put strawberry jello and pineapple mixed in refrigerator. Thaw strawberries and add Dream Whip to jello, pineapple mixture until whipped and blended.
Cool in refrigerator again.
Pinch up or poke cake and put mixture over cake.

title: leek, potato and tarragon soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy large pot over medium heat.
Add leeks, onion, garlic and 2 tbsp.
Water.
Cook until leeks are just golden, about 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and both; bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Mix in tarragon.
(Can be made 1 day ahead.)
Cool slightly.
Cover and refrigerate.
(Rewarm before continuing.) Stir in cream and yogurt.
Season soup to taste with salt and pepper. 4-6 servings.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Heat grill, or can be done in oven.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onions together.
Cook noodles until tender.
Mix cheese, English peas and mushroom soup together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Put in a baking dish.
Cook about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cookie crust pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
With lightly floured hands, press dough over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust, pressing dough as thin as possible on sides of pan.

title: corned bread pie casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Drain.
Add water, corn, soup and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole dish, 13 x 9.

title: hamburger with noodles*(diabetic)
directions: Spray Pam in large skillet.
Brown meat.
Combine milk and flour; add to meat mixture.
Add mushrooms, peas, parsley flakes and pepper.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Add noodles.
Cook until thick.

title: banana punch
directions: In blender, blend banana, and juice concentrate until smooth. Remove half the mixture and set aside.
Add 1 1/2 C water & 1 C sugar to mixture in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Place in large freezer container.
Repeat with remaining banana mixture, water & sugar.
Blend well.
Add to container.
Cover and freeze until solid.
One hour before serving remove from freezer.
Just before serving place in large punch bowl.
Add pineapple juice and soda. Stir until blended.
Garnish with orange slices.
Yield 10 quarts, 60-70 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil alternating sifted ingredients.
Add strawberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Flour and grease 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake in a bag.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and chill overnight.
Next day, add remaining ingredients to chicken mixture.
Toss and chill.

title: shrimp rarebit
directions: Melt grated cheese on low heat in a small saucepan, stirring constantly. When melted, add mayonnaise, stirring until blended. Add sour cream, lemon juice and paprika.
Blend. Remove from heat. Cut toast diagonally and arrange shrimp on toast.
Pour cheese on top and serve. Serves 4.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Crush vanilla wafers and eggs as you add to butter and sugar.
Add milk.
Fold in coconut and walnuts. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for two hours at 275°.

title: pepper steak
directions: In large skillet or wok, stir-fry the garlic in 1 tablespoon butter for 1 minute.
Add the onions and green peppers; stir-fry for 4 minutes, or until tender.
Remove vegetables to a bowl.
Add the remaining butter to pan.
Stir-fry steak until meat is cooked through, 3 minutes.
Return vegetables to wok or skillet.
Add the broth and soy sauce; bring to a boil.
Stir the water and cornstarch together in a cup; add to wok.
Cook, stirring, until the sauce is bubbly.
Cook for 2 minutes more.
Add the paprika, tomatoes and snow pea pods to the wok.
Cook the mixture for 30 seconds, stirring constantly to evenly distribute the sauce. Serve over rice, noodles or pasta.

title: saucy meatless balls
directions: Mix together; form into balls and brown in oil.
Or bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon pate spread
directions: In food processor with steel knife, mince parsley with on and off turns.
Transfer to a small bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: peanut butter cocoa cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and cream.
Stir and let come to boil (about 1 minute).
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: elsie's creole gumbo
directions: Fry bacon in large, deep iron skillet or heavy Dutch oven. Remove bacon.
To make roux, add flour gradually to grease, stirring constantly, until attain a medium gravy consistency, no more.
Discard any extra flour.
With practice, the roux can be made quickly over fairly high heat if you stir and watch it constantly.
If gets too thick, add touch of water or juice of tomatoes.
Cook until a rich dark golden brown color, but not burned.
Only then add onion and celery.
Turn to medium heat and cook until tender, adding some water, slowly thinning down roux mixture, keeping it smooth.
Add okra and add fresh tomatoes cut in pieces or several cut up canned tomatoes, no more.
Stir well, adding water to cover all ingredients.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and pineapple in a bowl.
Add pudding mix, lemon juice and reserved pineapple juice; mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, stir in bananas.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam. Add each ingredient as given and do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low calorie vegetable dip or dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve as a dip for raw vegetables or a dressing for a vegetable salad.
Makes 2 cups.

title: classic walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, syrup, butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake on lower shelf of oven at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour

title: baked beans
directions: Cook onions and garlic in bacon fat until onions are limp. Mix liquid and onions, then add beans. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour hot milk over oleo, honey and
salt;
let
cool until lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour, mix well; add dissolved yeast, oatmeal (uncooked) and stir in 2 more cups
of flour.
Knead in 1 to 3 cups flour until dough is soft and
elastic.
Let
rise
1 hour.
Punch down and let rise again for 15 minutes.
Shape into rolls; put in a greased pan and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and chop the avocado. Add the tomato, onion and pepper. Mix well and add the lemon juice and salt to taste. Serve with Mexican food or eat with tortilla chips.

title: ham-stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions; set aside. In a large skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Remove from the heat.
Add ham, mushrooms, half of the Swiss cheese and Parmesan; set aside.

title: reeses cups
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread evenly on top.
Chill 20 minutes, no longer. Then cut into squares.

title: feta cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix biscuit mix, eggs, buttermilk and salt until blended.
Spread in pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese and sesame seeds. Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares, then cut square diagonally into halves, forming triangles.
Garnish with olives.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Scrape strings and seeds out of pumpkin.
Layer slices of cheese and cream.
Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Put top back on pumpkin and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: caribbean meat balls
directions: Add onion, garlic, bread crumbs, milk, beaten egg yolks, salt, pepper and nutmeg to hamburger.
Beat egg whites stiff; fold into hamburger mixture.
Pinch off small bits and roll into tiny balls, keeping hands well-greased with cooking oil to ensure smooth balls.
Place, uncovered, in greased casserole dish.
Cook at 375° for 35 minutes.
Pour mushroom soup over top; bake for another 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Combine the ingredients in saucepan and cook and stir constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes. Add 1 1/3 cups of coconut and 1 cup pecans, chopped. Beat mixture until cool. Spread over German Chocolate Cake.

title: low carb chili
directions: Brown ground beef with pepper and onions.
Add in mushrooms. Add in remaining ingredients.
Simmer.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend in bananas and nuts. Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Add salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and turn out of pan after 10 minutes cooling.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix egg, shortening and milk thoroughly.
Combine mixtures and beat until mixed well.
Grease muffin pan and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes one dozen.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Grind cranberries; mix in sugar and marshmallows.
Set in icebox overnight, then mix in other ingredients.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together vanilla pudding, tapioca pudding and water.
Boil until clear.
Add orange jello.
Cool.
When cool, add Cool Whip and Mandarin oranges.
Mix together and chill.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent and onions together with hands (knead it like you would bread). Mix well. Dry pieces of ham with paper towels and spread cream cheese mixture to cover the whole piece. Roll ham long ways to give more slices per roll. Continue with same method until spread is gone. Refrigerate for 5 to 10 minutes to make slicing easier. Slice into small sizes and refrigerate until ready to serve. Serves about 20 to 25 people.

title: broccoli soup
directions: cook broccoli and onion slightly.
Add remaining ingredients. For a thinner soup add more milk.
Heat to boiling point.
Do Not boil.
Serves 10 - 12.

title: almond chicken francoise
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Cook green beans and drain well.
Mix yogurt, salt and pepper, mayonnaise, wine, parsley flakes, dill weed and garlic powder.
In 3 quart casserole dish layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 green beans, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 almonds, 1/2 Parmesan cheese and 1/2 yogurt mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste; drain.
Add flour and stir with meat.
Add can of soup and one can of water.
Add sour cream.
Add poppy seed and slivered almonds. (Fresh or canned, sliced mushrooms are optional.)
Cook Kluski noodles.
Add sauce and stir.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Wash and cook squash 3 to 4 minutes in boiling water and cool. Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter.
Add squash, cut into cubes. Add seasoning.
Mix eggs, then cheese.
Spoon into casserole pan. Dab with remaining butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili verde
directions: Place cubed tri-tip in crock-pot.
Cover tri-tip with water and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Drain water and pour chili verde over tri-tip.
Cover in crock-pot another 30 to 45 minutes. Great over cheese quesadillas.

title: quick and easy spread
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers of your choice.
Yields approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine water, cinnamon and salt.
Dribble this mixture over the apples.
Combine flour, sugar and butter with a pastry blender until crumbly. Spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in other ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix sugar and butter well.
Add flour.
Mix with mixer.
If dough is crumbly, mix 1 to 2 tablespoons milk in.
Press smoothly onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Good served with fresh fruit and whipped cream or ice cream.

title: everlasting salad
directions: Soak first 3 ingredients in salt and water for 1 hour.
Drain well and add celery.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Drain fruit; blend
sugar, cream cheese and salt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Combine
remaining
ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and freeze.

title: island-style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving syrup. In skillet, brown chicken. Pour off fat. Add reserved syrup, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy and garlic. Cover. Cook over low heat for 40 minutes. Add green peppers and pineapple chunks. Cook for 5 more minutes or until done. Stir occasionally.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Press 1 can of rolls into a greased sheet pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over rolls.
Press out other can of rolls and lay over mixture.
Brush on egg yolk.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely before cutting into small squares.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Toss with oil and add 2 cloves of garlic that have been minced.
Bake in shallow baking dish for 20 minutes at 400° until dark golden brown and fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Toss with chilled green salad.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Melt cheese.
Add tomatoes with chili peppers and ground beef.
Serve with any kind of corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: firecracker casserole
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients together for 10 minutes.
Spread in a 9x13 pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed above. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: the best mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut them into quarters.
Place in cold water in a large saucepan.
Boil until fork-tender; drain.
In a large bowl, mash the potatoes with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add the sour cream, cream cheese, only 5 tablespoons of the butter, milk and onion powder.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Turn into a greased baking dish and dot with the remaining butter. The casserole can be baked immediately or covered and kept in the refrigerator up to 48 hours.
To serve, bake uncovered at 400° until heated through and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
If chilled, bring the casserole to room temperature before baking.

title: bran cake
directions: Mix bran and milk (set aside).
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda and set aside.
Mix margarine, egg and bran mix together.
Stir in raisins and apples.
Divide batter into two greased pans or muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so; test with toothpick.
Cool and top with powdered sugar or cream cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, onion and 3/4 of the grated cheese.
Pour in a greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add remaining cheese and top with cereal.
Drizzle a stick of butter or oleo over the cereal.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable fettuccine
directions: Saute vegetables and garlic until crisp-tender.
Stir in beans, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook fettuccine separately according to directions.
Drain.
Combine fettuccine and vegetables and toss gently in Dutch oven.
Simmer until thoroughly heated.
Stir in 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Beat egg yolks and whipping cream until foamy.
Add to fettuccine and toss gently.
Heat until thickened. Pour in serving dish and add remaining Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle over top.

title: broccoli supreme casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Brown beef and season to taste.
Blend soup, flour, sour cream, 1/2 cup grated carrots, onion, pepper and salt.
Place broccoli in greased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Add meat and sprinkle rest of grated carrots over meat.
Spread soup mixture over top.
Combine stuffing mix with margarine.
Put over top and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown in a 350° oven.

title: rich chicken stock
directions: Bring chicken and water to a boil in a stockpot.
Reduce to a simmer, and skim off any scum that rises to the surface.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Strain and discard all solids.
Refrigerated, stock keeps for 3 to 4 days.
It also freezes well.
Makes approximately 3 quarts.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, oil, vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix all ingredients; fold in pie filling, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan; bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Wash and press water out of the artichokes.
Rinse chestnuts and cut into strips.
Add seasoning, mayonnaise and parmesan cheese.
Mix well, and put into baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips, Hawaiian bread or crackers.

title: children's delight
directions: Slowly melt together the almond bark and paraffin.
Make peanut butter crackers and dip in melted mixture.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Boil chicken and drain.
Clean chicken off bones in small pieces.
Add soup, sour cream and chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Crunch up crackers in small pieces and add melted butter and poppy seed.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab meat florentine
directions: Pick over crab meat.
Drain spinach.
Saute mushrooms over medium heat in large skillet until golden.
Blend in flour, garlic salt, pepper, sherry and milk.
Stir in sour cream, spinach and crab meat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Place in bowl and sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler about 5 inches from heat until melted and nicely browned (about 7 to 10 minutes).
Serves 4.
Good served with herbed rice.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix well together. Roll the mixture into balls. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana corn muffins
directions: Add combined banana, milk, oil and egg to combined dry ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill 12 greased or paper-lined medium-sized muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake in preheated hot oven (425°) for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place uncooked chicken wings in baking dish.
Pour rice over wings.
In separate bowl, mix mushroom soup, chicken soup, onion soup mix and water thoroughly.
Pour this mixture over rice and chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and spread shredded cheese on top.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 2-inches larger than inverted pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inches.
Ease into plate.
Flute edge.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain.
Stir in salt, oregano, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, onion and green pepper.
Spread in pie crust.
Beat egg and milk; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread over beef mixture.
Bake until crust is golden, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: aunt ann's christmas cake
directions: Cream together the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, food coloring and vanilla; mix.
Sift together, in separate bowl, the flour, salt and soda.
Add creamed mixture and dry ingredients, alternately, with the sour milk, then fold in soda dissolved in cider vinegar.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa; add to above mixture.
Add buttermilk and salt alternately with flour and vanilla.
Fold in soda and vinegar, which have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Fluff Frosting.

title: cold curried rice(side dish)
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as package directs; cool.
Dice artichokes and save juice.
Slice onions and olives.
Mix all ingredients and juice.
Refrigerate overnight or 24 hours.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Combine cranberries, apple and sugar and set aside.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add pineapple syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add cranberry/apple mixture, grapes, pineapple and nuts. Let chill until molded.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water in saucepan over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain raisins liquid into measuring cup; add water to make 1/2 cup.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisins liquid.
Blend flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into other ingredients.
Add rolled oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400°.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: danish coffee cake(makes 2; serves 10 to 12)
directions: Frosting:
Scald milk and butter.
Add salt, vanilla and sugar. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: tavern bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until granules dissolve.
Cool to 115°.
Put in large bowl.
Stir in yeast; let stand 5 minutes.
Add milk and next 4 ingredients.
