Stir in whole wheat flour and 1 cup all-purpose flour.
Beat with mixer for 1 minute.
Gradually add remaining 2 cups flour, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Divide dough into 4 well-greased 16 ounce cans. Let rise, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from cans immediately and cool on wire racks.
Yields 4 round loaves.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together by hand.
Melt oleo and chocolate over low heat.
Mix both mixtures together and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spoon into cupcake liners in muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno grits
directions: Add grits gradually to water and salt, stirring until thick, about 5 minutes.
Add eggs and let it come to a good boil.
Add margarine and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add Tabasco sauce.
Put in greased 8 or 9-inch square dish and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks and add flour, one teaspoon salt and a little pepper.
Add corn and fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop small spoonfuls on greased griddle or frying pan.
Do not cook too fast.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Saute onion, celery and poultry seasoning in margarine.
(Do not brown.)
Combine with corn bread crumbs and bread cubes.
Add parsley, salt and 1/2 to 3/4 cup of turkey broth.
Toss lightly with fork until well mixed.
Yields 8 cups to stuff a 15 pound turkey.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all together.
Roll dough and cut into strips.
Bake at 325° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: bacon cheddar dip
directions: Mix ingredients in serving bowl and sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Serve with chips.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread bread and raisins in 8-inch square baking dish.
Whisk 2 cups milk, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and salt in bowl.
Pour over bread.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Turn bread over once.
Whisk remaining milk, the egg, egg whites, vanilla, granulated sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour over bread. Sprinkle remaining brown sugar on top.
Place pan in larger pan and add water to come halfway up on smaller pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from water and let cool 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Measure milk into pan and blend in flour until no lumps remain.
Add margarine, onion and other seasonings and cook until sauce thickens.
Stir in macaroni and cheese.
Bake in greased 1-quart casserole, uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes or until slightly browned and bubbly.
May be frozen before baking.
Serves 4.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, flour and butter.
Roll in ball, put hole in middle of ball.
Fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown around edge.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix meal, flour, soda, salt and milk and blend well.
Beat 5 eggs well.
Mix in eggs and bake in oven at 450°.
Boil chicken with lots of water.
When done, debone and remove.
Mix cornbread with broth and add some light bread or biscuits.
Add 7 eggs (beaten) to bread mixture.
Mix in onions, celery and chicken. Add cream of chicken soup and can of water.
Bake at 350° to 450° until light brown.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil in glass bowl the sugar, margarine and salt. When it begins to boil, then boil for 2 minutes on Full power. Remove and add baking soda.
Pour over popcorn that has been put in a paper bag sprayed with Pam.
Shake up and put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake.
Put back in for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake, then pour on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix together, then pour into dish and chill, then add topping and keep in refrigerator.

title: swiss dip
directions: Cut off top of bread and scoop out insides, leaving 1-inch shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into hollow loaf.
Cut loaf top and insides of shell into bite size pieces for dipping.

title: heart attack cheesy hash brown potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Defrost hash browns just to the point where they are not a frozen solid block. Melt butter in a mixing bowl, add onion, then soup and sour cream, stir until combined. Mix in 2 cups of cheese, add salt and pepper. Stir in hash browns slowly. Spray casserole dish with Pam, place mixture in dish, sprinkle remaining cheese on top, then spray Pam on top. Cook for 45 minutes to one hour, less for more flavorful onions.

title: butterscotch treat
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.

title: poor boys hamburger
directions: Follow directions on "cheese and macaroni".
Fry hamburger, broken up in small pieces.
Add garlic and salt while frying. Combine macaroni; stir and serve.
Makes 5 servings.

title: brunch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: celery salad dressing
directions: Toss in blender and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Add all ingredients and shape into a ball.
Chill.

title: hobo sandwiches
directions: Brown sausage and beef; drain.
Mix in cheese until melted. Split dinner rolls and spread with mixture.
Toast in oven until warm.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix the Oreos, candy bars and oleo together well.
Put half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put ice cream over this. Sprinkle rest of mixture over ice cream.
Freeze.
Serves 7.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Add salad oil and continue beating.
Add oatmeal, corn flakes and coconut; mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool for a few minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Add almond flavoring. Mix sugars together.
Spray tube pan with Pam or grease and flour. Put sugars evenly in bottom of pan.
Place peach slices on top of sugar.
Cut margarine in pieces and put on top of sugar.
Pour batter over all and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, according to oven.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean when stuck in batter.

title: green chile chili
directions: Melt shortening in large deep skillet.
Brown floured meat thoroughly.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove cover.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes to desired consistency.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: kitchen sink salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Blend at low speed, then change to higher speed until mixed thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate.
This will keep for several weeks.

title: prairie fire dip
directions: Mix and heat over hot water (double boiler) until cheese is melted.

title: rigatoni with creamy tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil; saut 4 to 5 minutes. Add wine and cook for 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes, cream, olives, pasta and Parmesan cheese and toss well.
Sprinkle with green onion before serving.

title: creamy egg and vegetable casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter. Add flour. Slowly add water and milk, cooking until thickened. Add salt, onion, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Add all ingredients together, except egg whites.
Cook until thick and shiny.
Add to baked shell.
Use your favorite meringue. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Get oblong bowl and butter it all in the bottom and sides.
Get a rolling pin and crumb crackers up, then spread half of them in the bottom of bowl.
Pour half of the ingredients in the bowl and spread the other half of the crackers on top.
Put the rest on top of the crackers, then sprinkle crumbs on top of the whole dish. Cover and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey
directions: Marinate 6 to 24 hours in refrigerator.
Cook on grill, basting with marinade.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening together by hand.
Add eggs, water and bananas.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt and nuts and add to sugar mixture.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Pound cutlets until quite thin (between two pieces of plastic wrap).
Lay flat; spread prepared dressing to within 1/2-inch on each side of chicken; tightly roll and dip in egg and breadcrumbs. Fry slightly to brown in approximately 2 tablespoons of canola oil.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven. Makes 4 servings. before dipping and frying.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onion and pepper in margarine.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Place in oven at 375° or until cheese melts.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil; stir in raw peanuts and continue to stir until dry and peanuts are coated.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake about 35 minutes at 300°. Remove from oven and cool.

title: gardun casserole
directions: Zucchini iz the long green squash thet she usually sliced 'n rolled in 1 cuppa meal, 2 tablespoons flour, 2 aigs, salt 'n pepper...'n then fried in shortenin' 'n bak on grease.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald 3 cups of milk and pour onto corn meal.
Cook in double boiler 15 minutes.
Add molasses, salt, sugar, spices and butter.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add in order given.
Bake in slow oven (325°) in uncooked pie shell for 1 hour.

title: herbes de provence
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a jar.
Use in scrambled eggs and sauce or on meat, seafood or poultry.

title: chicken with peppers and spaghetti
directions: Melt butter; stir in onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook until peppers are crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon; set aside.
Add chicken, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook until chicken is slightly browned and tender (approximately 7 to 9 minutes).
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
When chicken is cooked, add vegetables, half and half, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Reduce heat and cook until cheese is melted.
Add to cooked spaghetti and toss gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesy hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in glass container; bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: mango bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking soda and lima juice.
Beat in mangos.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in lightly greased and floured loaf pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in cooking oil until transparent.
Then add remaining ingredients in order given.
Simmer about 30 minutes before using.
Makes 2 cups.

title: 4-4-4-1 sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; cook over high heat 15 minutes; stir frequently.
Reduce to medium heat; cook until sauce is almost dry and meat is tender.
Remove excess oil before serving.
You may adjust the sauce according to your personal taste.

title: german chocolate special
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Punch holes in it and pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over entire cake.
Layer with 1 small carton Cool Whip.
Grate large Hershey bar on top.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onions, celery and green pepper together.
Mix the soups, water, milk, rice and the pimentos together.
Mix all together and put in a baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup until smooth. Gradually add milk.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange layer of potatoes, onion and sauce. Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, covered, 1 hour at 375°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cut sliced onion into quarters.
Cook onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is transparent.
Add flour and cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken stock and cook for approximately 10 minutes, stirring until smooth.
Add wild rice, cream and sherry, stirring until heated throughout.
Garnish with parsley. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy beef bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese mix. Brown meat and onion in the margarine in a skillet. Stir the soup and milk in with the meat and onion. In a greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole, layer the Kraft dinner and meat mixture, then repeat the layers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 4-6.

title: heath bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil butter and sugar together 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour chocolate chips over top of crackers evenly.
Return to oven until chips melt.
Cool.
Break into squares.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Add sour cream and vanilla, then fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and put topping of cherries on before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken arlette
directions: Pound chicken.
Spread with butter, pepper and cheese, then roll up and secure with a couple of toothpicks.
Roll in flour and egg, then bread crumbs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick butter with garlic.
Add wine; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with fettuccine or noodles.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Wash potatoes and put in a large cook pot; cover with water and boil (add water as needed to keep covered) about 40 minutes or until done.
Drain and let cool.
When cool, peel and coarsely chop into large bowl.
Mash well and add all ingredients.
Mix well to blend.
Pour into shells.
Bake 15 minutes in a 425° preheated oven, then for 40 minutes in a 350° oven until filling is set and a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cover crust with foil if edges start to brown too fast.
Makes two 9-inch pies. Freeze any leftover batter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and seasoning.
Shape into loaf (8 x 4-inch).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Blend remaining soup, water and 3 tablespoons drippings.
Heat just to boiling.
Pour over meat loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Defrost broccoli but do not cook.
Mix together broccoli, onion and rice.
Slice butter into pats and mix into broccoli.
Mix together in separate bowl the soup, milk and half of the cheese.
Fold into broccoli mixture.
Salt to taste. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve hot.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine hot mashed potatoes with all other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: swiss steak deluxe
directions: Pound 6 tablespoons flour into steak. Brown in hot fat.
Add above ingredients. Cover and cook over very low heat or in oven at 275° to 300° until tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to cook down sauce.

title: texas cake(serves 24)
directions: Mix in bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil in saucepan, margarine, cocoa and water.
Mix into flour mixture slowly, beating well.
Pour the mixture into a greased jellyroll type pan.
(Batter should be about 1 1/2 inches deep in pan.) Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (don't overbake).

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Into a bowl, sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast mixture.
Stir until all flour is moist.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together good, then roll in a log.
Wrap and refrigerate. Slice in 1/4-inch slices and bake in a 350° oven.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Put all ingredients, including uncooked ground beef, into a large pot.
Fill with water to top of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: broiled fish
directions: Put fish on a greased baking dish.
Brush with melted butter. Combine remaining ingredients.
Broil fish about 4 inches from heat for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; spread evenly with cheese mixture.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes longer, until light brown.

title: butterscotch cream cheese bars
directions: Melt morsels and butter in medium, heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir until smooth. Stir in crumbs and walnuts.
Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar slowly. Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Cut gumdrops in small pieces.
Mix with raisins and nuts. Use a small portion of dry ingredients that you have mixed all together. Mix applesauce with water and add with the dry ingredients. Then mix real good.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: parmesan caraway appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients until stiff dough forms.
Drop by slightly rounded teaspoon about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs and oil in small mixing bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, powder, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Add egg mixture; mix well.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Spread icing on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells.
Makes two pies.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pie
directions: Stir whip cream and milk together in a large mixing bowl. Pour drained fruit into whip cream mixture and beat with mixer until peaches are in small pieces. Pour into vanilla wafer crust. Makes 2 pies.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs in mixture until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and slowly add milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients well.
Pour into greased 13 x 5-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread while hot with peanut butter.
Cool cake in refrigerator.
Frost with melted chocolate or chocolate frosting.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together.
Boil 6 minutes to soft ball stage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer about 1 minute.
Pour into buttered 11 x 17-inch pan.
Cut when cooled.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Melt the marshmallows and milk together (I use microwave). Add the butter and let stand.
Drain the pineapple.
Add the whipping cream.
Mix and add to first mixture.
Spread the graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour mixture over them.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Set egg whites aside.
Beat egg yolks and add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add liquids.
Mix well.
Cook on medium, stirring constantly.
Cook to medium thickness.
Add vanilla to taste.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold gently into cooked mixture.
Put into jars and refrigerate.
May add nutmeg if desired.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Debone chicken and add to broth.
Make dumplins using canned biscuits.
Roll flat and cut into small pieces.
Need about 20 to 30 dumplins.
Boil chicken and broth about 10 minutes or until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Drop in dumplins one at a time and continue cooking until dumplins are done.

title: apple banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream applesauce and sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix yogurt and vanilla.
Add egg whites and beat thoroughly.
Add mixture to applesauce and sugar; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine dry ingredients; mix until well blended.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 1 loaf (16 slices).

title: audrey's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients (except ketchup) thoroughly and pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.
Top with ketchup to taste before baking, if desired.

title: quicky sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Pull thawed bread into walnut size pieces.
Fill pan (single layer). Heat together other ingredients until well mixed.
Pour over the dough and let rise in refrigerator overnight or at room temperature about 3 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: avocado and bacon sandwich
directions: Blend mayonnaise with lemon juice to spread on toast.
Top with avocado and bacon.
Makes 8.

title: corn bread
directions: Note:
Substitute 1 cup blue corn meal for 1 cup corn meal for something different!

title: bobotee
directions: Soak bread in half the milk.
Fry onion in 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Mix curry powder, sugar, salt, lemon juice and add to hamburger.
Add soaked bread, fried onions, chopped almonds and 1 egg.
Mix well and put into well greased dish.
Whisk the remaining two eggs and rest of the milk.
Season with salt and pepper and pour over the hamburger mixture.
Put some sliced lemons on top with the rest of the margarine (melted).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° standing in a dish of water.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in large saucepan.
Add onions, celery and green peppers.
Saute, stirring often until onions are transparent.
(May need to turn heat to low.
Add more butter if needed)

title: chili beef and biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef with onions and green peppers (salt to taste).
Drain fat.
Add sauce and seasonings. Simmer 10 minutes or more.
Separate biscuits.
Pull each apart into 2 layers.
Press 1 layer over bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Spoon on meat mixture.
Spread second layer of biscuit halves on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lime salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cottage cheese and stir.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: no frosting banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, eggs and vanilla together.
Add mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Scrape down bowl. Blend in flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Put into 2 (8-inch) round cake tins.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve warm.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Cream together taco seasoning, cream cheese and sour cream spread in 10 x 15 1/2 in. pan.
Sprinkle cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Use tortilla chips to dip.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with 2/3 cup sugar; let stand 1 hour. Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, 3 tablespoons sugar, margarine and milk until soft dough forms.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls into 6 mounds on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Split shortcakes; spoon strawberries between halves and over tops.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: heavenly cream cheese bars
directions: Mix together until crumbly the brown sugar, margarine, biscuit mix and nuts.
Save 3 cups and press remainder into baking pan. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile, mix together the cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Return to oven and bake about 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Crumble crackers over the top of the casserole.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine in large pan over medium heat.
Remove from heat; add flour and stir until smooth.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until light brown.
Add paprika, salt, pepper, garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add oysters and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut pecan sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, egg yolks and margarine.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, about 8 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Cook on microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir after 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Put in freezer for 20 minutes.

title: coconut pie(makes own crust)
directions: Melt margarine and beat together with sugar and eggs.
Add milk, coconut and flavoring.
Grease 10-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kobi's shrimp sauce
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pineapple raccoon
directions: Blow raccoon hair off counter!
Grease 1-quart casserole dish with a light film of the melted butter.
Mix well between additions.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Add strained, crushed pineapple.
Add cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix crackers and melted butter.
Pour on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Mix in blender. Chill and serve.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pecans and coconut.
Place in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Spoon over pecan mixture.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: In saucepan, melt together mushroom soup and cheese.
Add broccoli.
When all this is heated thoroughly add mushrooms. Serve warmed in a fondue pot or in crock-pot.
Best with Tostitos chips.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Mix until well blended.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Makes 4 dozen.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate almond meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites with vinegar and salt until stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating until meringue stands in stiff peaks.
Fold in flavorings, nuts and chopped chocolate.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in very slow (250°) oven for about 30 minutes, or until firm to touch.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
While cookies bake, combine the 1 square chocolate and water in top of double boiler.
Place over hot water and heat until chocolate is melted.
Stir to blend.
Drizzle over cookies when removed from oven.
Yield:
About 5 dozen cookies.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Season meat; add onion, rice and egg.
Roll a portion of filling into each leaf; fasten ends with toothpicks.
Place the cabbage rolls in the pressure cooker.
Pour tomato soup and water over rolls.
Cover, set control and cook 8 minutes after pressure is reached.
Let pressure go down normally.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on medium heat until syrup turns caramel color (approximately 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 teaspoons soda.
Stir well and pour onto well buttered tinfoil and spread with back of spoon.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: mother's pecan cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing.
Freezes well.
Bake in greased and floured pan.

title: date bars
directions: Mix and cook in heavy saucepan, stirring often until thick, the dates, water and sugar.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put in buttered casserole dish and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Top with can of Durkee French fried onions.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Cook broccoli 1 minute on High in microwave and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except corn bread mix.
Then add mix.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix drained tuna, egg and crackers.
Form into 4 patties.
Fry slowly on both sides.
Serve on buns, spread with tartar sauce.

title: lemon buttermilk pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dice cantaloupe.
Combine fruits and use sauce as poppy seed dressing.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix lemon juice and water well.
Then place chicken (cut up into strips) in the water-lemon mixture and let soak for 20 minutes.

title: pickled peach salad
directions: Drain peaches, saving 1 cup juice.
Heat juice and dissolve jello.
Add water, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cut up peaches and add peaches and nuts to mixture; congeal.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables as directed on packages.
Add cheese, margarine and mix until cheese is melted.
Place in 2-quart oblong casserole.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Add cracker crumbs and stir until coated.
Spread over top of vegetable mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
(Broccoli or Brussels sprouts may be substituted for cauliflower.)
May be made day before and refrigerated before baking.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Potatoes should be defrosted.
Pour into oiled casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If topping is desired, mix 2 cups crushed cornflakes and 1/4 cup margarine.
Sprinkle on top before baking.

title: molasses cake
directions: Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients; save 1/2 cup for top of cake.
Mix in liquids.
Put 1/2 cup of dry ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apple filling in buttered 9-inch square pan.
In bowl, beat eggs, add condensed milk, melted margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Pour over apple filling.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and flour, cut in cold margarine until crumbly.
Add nuts and oats.
Sprinkle on top. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Serve warm or cold. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and milk together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Stud orange with cloves.
Cut in half.
Pour cider or juice in a large kettle or pot; float orange and cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil; heat for 30 minutes.
Remove to a crock-pot (optional) to keep warm.
Serve hot.
Makes 16 cups.

title: summer time ribs
directions: Cook
ribs
in
water
first
to
make
them tender and shortens grill time.
In large pot or Dutch oven combine ribs, vinegar, onion, peppercorns, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for one hour.
Drain; cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator
1 hour
before
grilling.
Prepare grill.
Grill ribs 10 minutes, turning once.
Baste with barbecue sauce.
Grill for 5 more minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend together in blender and serve.
Makes approximately five 5 oz. servings.

title: pickle corn
directions: Cut corn off of cob and fill quart jar and add the sugar, vinegar and salt.
Fill jar with cold water.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into a hot greased skillet.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about two dozen.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil and butter in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning, until browned on all sides. Remove chicken and set aside.
Pour off and discard all but 3 tablespoons drippings.

title: nutty peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, margarine, sugar and Marshmallow Creme in a heavy saucepan (3-quart size).
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
After it comes to a boil, continue stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add peanut butter chips and vanilla, stirring until chips are melted.
Add nuts. Pour into a buttered 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cool.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread in pieces and place in greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Brown and drain sausage; spoon over bread. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over sausage. Beat together eggs, milk and salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. The cheese will rise to the top during baking.

title: orange pineapple drink
directions: Mix orange juice and pineapple juice together.
Freeze part of mixture into cubes.
Then mix in 7-Up and/or Sprite.
Chill. Serve with frozen juice cubes.

title: whacky snacky
directions: In small bowl, blend butter and cinnamon.
In large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels (or Teddy Grahams) and peanuts.
Toss with margarine mixture onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once.
Remove from oven; stir in raisins and coconut.
Store tightly covered for up to 1 week.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and leave skins on.
Drop in hot peanut oil and cook until golden brown; remove.
Use seasoned salt, sprinkled light.
Then eat.
Good!

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix soup, milk and cheese.
Pour half of the mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Separate rolls.
Place cut up chicken into crescent rolls, tucking in edges.
Place in pan. Spoon remaining mixture over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top will be lightly browned when done.

title: cabbage patch vegetable dip
directions: Empty package of Lipton soup mix into a large bowl.
Pour sour cream into the bowl, too.
Stir well.
Add lemon juice, mayonnaise and chopped spinach.
Mix well.
Core the cabbage head in the middle, scooping out the center, but leaving a solid portion to form a bowl with the cabbage.
Save some of the leaves and shred on a grater.
Add shredded leaves to sour cream and mix well. Spoon mixture into the head of cabbage.

title: rhubarb relish
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb into 1-inch pieces.
Peel and chop onions quite fine.
Combine all ingredients; boil gently until fairly thick.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: pasta tutto mare(all sea)
directions: Heat oil in saucepan and add garlic and rosemary.
Cook until brown.
Remove browned garlic and rosemary.
Add all seafood, parsley and lemon juice.
Simmer for 7 minutes.
Do not overcook. Cook pasta al dente and drain.
Tos with half of seafood sauce and spoon the remainder over separate portions before they are served. Serves 8 to 10.

title: ham and asparagus divine
directions: Slice ham 1/4 inch thick.
Cook asparagus until tender; drain. Alternate slices of ham and asparagus in a shallow baking dish. Melt margarine; stir in flour, milk and sour cream.
Stir in Muenster cheese; cook until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over ham and asparagus.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; bake in 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until top is brown. Serve hot.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; add squash, onion, pepper and celery.
Stir constantly until squash is tender.
Add tomatoes (if fresh cook a few minutes longer).
Add salt and oregano.
Remove from heat; add cheese and corn.
Pour into a buttered casserole and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° until lightly brown.

title: budget fruit punch
directions: Mix powdered drink mix by directions on envelope with sugar and water.
Add juices.
Chill.
Add ginger ale before serving. Serves 35 to 40.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pork-yam-apple casserole
directions: Brown pork.
Bake yams in skin.
Pull off skins after cooling enough to handle after baking.
Peel apples.
Slice.
Season with cinnamon.

title: coffee dunkers(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Cover tightly and let stand 3 to 4 hours at room temperature.
Form dough into 24 (1 x 4 1/2-inch) wiener shaped rolls.
Bake on medium-high in waffle iron for 2 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature until hard.
(May be frozen but allow to harden after thawing.)

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil the celery in just enough water to cover it for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add to the drained celery the cream of mushroom soup and the melted butter; mix.
Pour in a casserole pan. Sprinkle the bread crumbs and the almonds and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: recipe for a happy day
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add heaping cups of understanding. Use generous amount of time and patience.
Cook on low.
Do not boil.
Add generous dash of humor and a pinch of warm personality. Season to taste with Word of Life, God's Holy Bible.
Serve in individual molds with lots of prayerful thought.

title: oatmeal cinnamon buns
directions: Let rise again and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mustard sauce for ham
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on medium heat until thickened, stirring to prevent lumping.
Serve warm.
Sauce keeps well in refrigerator and may be reheated successfully.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Put rice and water in baking dish.
Stir in onion soup mix and extra onion.
Place meat on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in greased baking dish.
Top with cubed chicken or turkey.
Combine soup and milk until blended.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Wash chicken well, pat dry; coat with flour.
Heat oil in large skillet or wok, brown on all sides.
Remove as browned to shallow baking dish or roasting pan, skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients. Knead well.
Shape into a roll.
Place in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes (no longer).

title: rice excellente
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet.
Add the onion, mushrooms, water chestnuts, celery and green pepper. Saute about 5 minutes. Add the poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, prepare the wild rice mix according to the package directions.
Combine cooked rice thoroughly with the vegetable mixture.
Yields 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons flour with salt.
Cut beef across grain into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Dredge beef in flour mixture.
Melt butter.
Add beef and cook on medium high heat to quickly brown on all sides.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes until onion is tender.
Remove mixture and use drippings and extra butter if needed to make the sauce.
Blend in 6 tablespoons flour until soft dry paste.
Add tomato paste and mix well.
Add beef broth slowly and stir quickly to avoid lumps.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Return meat mix to sauce.
Stir in sherry and sour cream.
Heat briefly.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: garbanzo spread(fat free recipe)
directions: Mix everything together and let blend for an hour or two. Good served in pita pockets with sprouts, chopped onion and tomatoes.
Great for campers.

title: tulsa punch
directions: Make a syrup of water and sugar.
Boil 15 minutes and cool. Mix syrup with remaining ingredients.
Freeze to a slushy consistency before mixing with 7-up or ginger ale.
Mix 50% slush to 50% 7-up/ginger ale.
The punch is much better slushy.
May want to freeze the juice mixture fairly firm and don't mix remainder until just before serving.

title: cream cheese fish rolls
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until tender. Stir together cheese, onion, mushrooms and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs. Between 2 sheets of waxed paper, roll fish thin.
Spread cheese mixture over flattened fish.
Roll and secure with toothpick, if necessary.
If fish is smaller and will not roll, sandwich cheese between 2 pieces of fish.
Dip in beaten egg and coat with bread crumbs. Saute in butter approximately 5 to 10 minutes on each side until fish is done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In a
saucepan, mix the sugar, white vinegar, oil, salt and pepper together.
Bring to a boil, stirring for 2 minutes. Remove from
heat. Cool completely and pour over vegetables in a large bowl.
Refrigerate	2 to 3 hours or overnight for best flavor. Will keep several weeks, covered, in refrigerator.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Combine crumbs with butter; press firmly onto bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Stir gelatin into boiling water until completely dissolved.
Add ice cubes.
Stir until gelatin thickens.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Add Cool Whip and stir with wire whisk until blended.
Gently stir in peaches.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes to thicken.
Spoon into pie crust and refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart bowl.
Cook 5 minutes on High in microwave.
Stir in nuts; cook 2 minutes.
Stir; cook for 2 minutes.
Stir; cook 2 minutes.
Stir; cook 2 minutes. Stir; 13 minutes in all.
At once add margarine and vanilla.
Add soda last.
Mix will be foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Spread thin.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: party pink salad
directions: Drain juice from can of pineapple.
Mix juice with 24 marshmallows.
Place over low heat until marshmallows dissolve. Remove; add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, chopped nuts and cherries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Turn down to 300° until knife comes out clean.

title: baked cushaw(crook-necked squash)
directions: Cut cushaw in pieces, scrape out seed and boil until tender. Remove peeling.
Mix cushaw with the rest of the ingredients. Place in baking dish and bake in 350° oven until brown on top.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Dice the unpeeled cored red eating apples. Sprinkle apples with lemon juice to prevent darkening. Mix with the celery, walnuts and a little mayonnaise.
Chill.
Serve in lettuce cups. Makes 4 servings.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mesh in wooden bowl the first 7 ingredients. Stir all ingredients together. Toss lettuce together with dressing mixture. Add ground pepper, croutons and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: candied pecans
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat until mixture forms a soft ball, about 10 minutes.
(Use a candy thermometer, it's much easier!!)
Do not stir while cooking.

title: peas and peanuts salad
directions: Turn peas into colander.
Run hot water over to thaw.
Combine peas, cabbage and onion in bowl.
In separate bowl, blend sour cream, mayo, salt, curry powder, pepper, mustard and vinegar. Pour over cabbage mixture; mix lightly.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Pour peanuts over top of salad; toss lightly just before serving.

title: cowboy chili
directions: Crumble beef into heavy pot or Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook over medium to high heat until meat is browned, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, beef broth, chili powder, cumin, oregano leaves, salt and cayenne.
Cover, simmer, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Add beans.
Simmer 30 minutes longer. Add water, if the chili becomes too thick.
Serve piping hot.

title: holiday rice pudding
directions: In large saucepan, combine milk,
water and the 1/4 cup sugar; bring to a boil over high
heat;
stir in rice.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, about 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove
from
heat; stir in butter and almond flavoring until
well
combined.
Cool; whip cream; beat in 1 tablespoon
sugar.
Fold	cream
and
almonds into pudding; cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving. Serve with raspberry jam or sauce.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello using boiling water.
Add cold water or juice. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in glass dish and refrigerate.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt butter in oven, then remove.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Mix together and press into pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 24 bars.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water (to cover).
Cook 10 minutes and drain.
Put stuffing and season packet in large bowl.
Add melted oleo and mix.
Save 1/2 cup of stuffing mixture.
Add squash and onion, sour cream , carrots and soup to stuffing mixture and mix well.
Put in buttered casserole.
Put the 1/2 cup of plain stuffing on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: curry chicken with fresh fruit(1 serving)
directions: Cook chicken breast; cool and dice into medium size pieces. Set aside.
Saute curry powder, almonds, raisins and brown sugar over medium heat just until almonds brown.
Let cool slightly.
Add mayonnaise and then mix in chicken.
Serve cold on a platter with fresh fruit.

title: scrambled bacon
directions: Have mommy or daddy cook bacon and scramble eggs.
Then mix together and enjoy.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add rest of stuff.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat tortillas in cooking oil until soft; drain.
Put 1 tablespoon of chopped onion and 2 tablespoons of shredded cheese in tortilla and roll.
Place down.
Melt margarine in heavy skillet; add flour and stir.
Add broth and cook until thick.
Add sour cream, green chilies and chicken and stir until heated.
Pour over tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cook 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes at once down through cake to the pan with round handle of a wooden spoon or with a straw, using a turning motion to make large holes at 1-inch intervals.

title: french-style green pea casserole
directions: Combine green peas with soup and mushrooms in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle top of casserole with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hungry now supper
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
While beef is cooking, cube peeled potatoes and stick in microwave until tender (5 to 10 minutes).

title: custard crunch mince pie
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, then butter and mincemeat and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 30 minutes.
If mincemeat is real thick, add 2 tablespoons water.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on greased 10 x 15 pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix next 5 ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Cut up vegetables into bite-size pieces and spread on top. Chill.
Use any or all of the following vegetables listed:

title: carrot cake and frosting
directions: Beat sugar, vegetable oil and eggs.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes at 325°.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt.
Add to the beaten eggs. Beat until smooth.
Stir in the rhubarb.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch 2 crust pie.
Fill pastry with rhubarb mixture.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Seal.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes. Scrumptious.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine salt and ice water for brine. Cover vegetables with brine. Let set in refrigerator 48 hours. Drain well but do not rinse. Add syrup and put in containers and freeze.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Combine juice and boiling water; bring to a boil.
Pour over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Chill.
When almost set, stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: m. j. pumpkin bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients including sugar.
Add oil.
Blend in nuts.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or in a 17 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix
first 4 ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Bring water and salt to a boil.
Drop meatballs into water.
When they float to top, remove and drain.
Put in crock-pot or loaf pan. Pour over favorite sauce and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
(We like barbecue sauce best.)

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on until soft.
Fry bacon crisp. Crumble.
Dice onions.
Cube cheese.
Cut up potatoes and mix everything together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake covered at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake until brown or about 10 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Pour 1/4 of melted margarine over cracker crumbs. Saute onions in remaining margarine. Layer crumbs and onions, ending with crumbs. Mix eggs, flour and milk; pour over onions and cracker crumbs. Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to cream mixture.
Fold in vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove while cake is hot.
Spread with marshmallow cream.
Let cool.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In large skillet, saut zucchini and carrots in olive oil until tender.
Stir in spinach. In medium bowl, combine Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix well.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper together until done.
Add all other ingredients, reserving 1/3 cup cheese and 1/3 cup crushed chips.
Mix well; pour into casserole dish and top with remaining cheese and chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Needs to be a little soupy before adding crushed chips; if not, can add a little more water.

title: four day cake(great make ahead)
directions: Make a yellow or banana cake according to directions.
Bake in round pans.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, powdered sugar and coconut.
Cool cake.
Split into four layers and frost with mix. Cover tightly and store in the refrigerator for up to 4 days.

title: barbecue sauce(for roast pork)
directions: Boil 1 minute.
This sauce is good to simmer hot dogs in.
Or use over pork chops or any pork meat.

title: popcorn ala poppycock
directions: Combine butter, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and nuts.
Stir until well coated.
Pour into baking pan and bake in a 250° oven until dry, stirring every 20 minutes. Should take 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Cut bread in 5 or 6 sticks.
Toast in slow oven 250° or 300° for about 30 minutes.
Toast the crusts and ends at the same time, and put them in a blender or roll out and make crumbs.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna; drain and rinse with cold water.
Beat 2 eggs; add cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
To assemble lasagna, pour a thin layer of meat mixture in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with layer of lasagna noodles.
Spread half the cheese mixture over lasagna. Lay half the Mozzarella cheese over the cheese mixture.
Spread a layer of tomato sauce over all.
Repeat layers; top with remaining lasagna and tomato sauce.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes; uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: savory barbecued short ribs
directions: Combine ribs with about 1-inch salted water in large saucepan. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender; drain.
Combine gravy mix, water, lemon juice, oil, catsup and brown sugar.
Brush over ribs.
Grill over hot coals 15 to 20 minutes, turning frequently and brushing with sauce until well browned.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Break Hershey bars into pieces.
Mix in a 6 to 8-quart container with Hershey Dainties, vanilla, marshmallow cream and butter.
Mix the sugar and evaporated milk in a 4 to 6-quart saucepan and bring to a boil.
After it starts to boil, cook for 6 minutes.
Pour mixture of sugar and evaporated milk over remaining ingredients and blend until smooth and creamy.
After mixture is completely blended, add the chopped nuts.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch square dish.
Put sugar and cocoa in a microwave bowl; stir.
Add milk and butter.
Do not stir.
Heat, uncovered, at full power for 2 minutes.
Stir to blend.
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: baked fish
directions: Dip fish in canola oil and roll in crumbs.
Put on oiled pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 500° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pilaf casserole
directions: Follow directions on package for rice but do not let rice cook all the way, leave it slightly soupy and set aside.

title: cream cheese lemon pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter and cream cheese in large mixing bowl.
Add 2 eggs, 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar.
Mix slowly until blended.
Repeat this procedure until all ingredients are blended together.
Add extract and stir well.
Pour batter into a Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: country meat loaf
directions: Saute celery and onion in vegetable oil.
In large bowl, break bread and add onion, celery, ground beef, shredded carrot, egg and half of can of tomato sauce.
Stir and blend thoroughly.
Shape in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen green beans according to package directions; drain. Gently stir in 2 cans cream of mushroom soup.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle over top 1 can French fried onions. Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven.
Serves 6.

title: creamy raspberry dessert
directions: Crush cookies and spread on bottom of a
9 x 13-inch or larger baking dish.
Melt 1 stick butter; mix with cookie crumbs.
Cream 1 1/2 sticks butter; add sugar and egg yolks and beat until fluffy and light.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then blend into sugar-butter mixture.
Spoon over cookie crumbs.
Cover cream with pie filling.
Cover with whipped cream.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Lightly butter a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking sheet with raised sides; set aside.
In a 2-quart bowl, combine sugar and syrup. Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until syrup turns a light brown color.
Stir in peanuts, butter or margarine and vanilla until blended.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Place bowl on hot pad. Syrup will be very hot.
Gently stir in baking soda until mixture is light and foamy.
Pour evenly onto prepared baking sheet; let cool 30 to 60 minutes.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound

title: barb's blueberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Add blueberries and pineapple with juice. Chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Spread on top of jello.
Sprinkle with pecans.
This recipe will serve 7 people.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in shortening and drain.
Combine pineapple juice, water, vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar and salt.
Pour over meat and simmer 1 hour.
Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water. Add to meat and cook until thickened.
Add pineapple chunks, onion and green pepper.
Cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put sugar and cornstarch in first.
Mix and then add eggs.
Next the corn and milk.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttersweet brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Put 1/2 cup nuts into blender and process until chopped.
Empty into mixing bowl. Repeat with remaining nuts.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl with nuts.
Set aside.
Put eggs, butter, sugar, vanilla and chocolate into blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Pour over flour mixture and mix until well blended.
Spread in prepared pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.
Cut in bars or squares.
Yields 24.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Melt butter or margarine in an 8 or 9-inch round or square pan in oven while it heats to 400°.
When margarine is melted, remove pan from oven.
Add brown sugar and spread over pan bottom.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
(Kitchen scissors work well for this.)

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Add other ingredients. Put in a crock-pot and simmer.
Stir to blend as cheese melts.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast until tender.
Pull from bones and cube meat.
Add sufficient water, bouillon cube, salt, pepper and parsley flakes to chicken broth.
Bring to boil and add noodles. Cook noodles thoroughly.
Do not drain.
Add the soups and chicken to noodles.
Stir thoroughly and turn into casserole and bake for a few minutes, 20 to 30 minutes, at 350°.
Top should be lightly brown.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl and mix.
Then form into patties.
Cook on grill for approximately 15 to 20 minutes. Top with favorite hamburger toppings.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate filled cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugars, shortening, butter, vanilla and egg in a large bowl. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Mold 2 level teaspoonfuls of dough around each star.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 6 to 7 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: mushrooms polonaise
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place mushrooms and onion in a heavy nonstick skillet with a tiny bit of olive oil. Cook slowly until wilted but not browned. Add 1/2 cup of butter. When butter has melted, add flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes over very low heat. Stir in sour cream and heavy cream with a wooden spoon, then add nutmeg and pepper to taste. Continue to cook, uncovered until mixture has thickened. Stir in parsley. In another pan, lightly saute bread crumbs in 1/4 cup of butter. Pour mushroom mixture into a buttered shallow casserole. Sprinkle top with sauteed bread crumbs. Bake until mixture has set and bread crumbs have browned a little more.

title: thick cheese sauce
directions: Melt the butter in a small enameled iron saucepan or a double boiler.
Add the flour and blend well.
Add cheese and beat until smooth.
Slowly add the milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until the sauce is thick and perfectly smooth, approximately 4 minutes.
Add salt and cayenne pepper.

title: irene's sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for an hour.
If too much liquid, add 3 or 4 tablespoons of uncooked oats and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Mix all ingredients and leave in refrigerator 24 to 48 hours. Preheat oven to 300°.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vanilla and raisins to the eggs (set aside for 1 hour).
Cream margarine and artificial sweetener.
Add to egg, vanilla and raisin mixture.
Sift flour with salt, nutmeg, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Add this mixture to the other mixture and stir well.
Add oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Don't overbake. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: nifty nachos
directions: Stack tortillas.
Cut the stack into 8 wedges to make a total of 40 wedges.
Spread wedges evenly in single layer on 2 medium baking sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until wedges are dry and crisp.

title: kim chee sandwich
directions: Spread mayonnaise on both pieces of bread.
Lay single slice of cheese on bread.
Lay Kim Chee over the cheese, covering the bread.
Lay sliced tomatoes over the Kim Chee and sprinkle the tomatoes with salt.
Cover the tomatoes with the other slice of bread.
Now go for it and broke mouth...

title: zucchini milano
directions: In a large pan, melt butter.
Add onion, green pepper and oregano.
Saute until tender.
Add zucchini; cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in tomato.
Turn heat very low and stir in cheese until melted.

title: apple pie cake
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine. Remove from heat; blend in sugar and egg. Add remaining ingredients; blend well. Put in greased floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine potatoes, 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 the onions; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading across bottom and up sides to form a shell.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour into potato shell.

title: greater tater casserole
directions: Mix potatoes with soup and onions.
Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with foil the last 15 minutes.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix and cook in double boiler until begins to thicken, then pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until pie is firm.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Add applesauce and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add sugar. Mix and let cool. Add cheese, pecans, pineapple and chopped nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex and allow to set. Mix bell pepper, green onions and mayonnaise. Spread on top of congealed mixture.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Place first six ingredients in large sauce pan.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover, simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender; cool.
Blend until uniform.
Strain to remove large pieces.
Pour into large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise and whipping cream with whisk.
Chill at least 16 hours.
Serve in icers.

title: cheese roll
directions: Warm cheese (do not melt).
Mix altogether with mixer.
Form into roll and refrigerate.

title: mom's chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Brown almonds and sesame seed on cookie sheet for maybe 10 minutes at 350°.
Watch carefully.
Take out and let cool.
Mix dressing, chicken, lettuce, cabbage, onions and almond and sesame seed all together.
Enjoy; this is a wonderful salad.

title: irish rose banana dessert loaf
directions: Blend bananas, then add everything else.
Mix until moist. Spread into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: turkey surprise
directions: Line baking dish with meat, already cooked and boned.
Mix sour cream, soup and milk.
Pour over meat.
Top with stuffing and bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: rice balls
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Roll in flour; drop in boiling tomato juice.
Reduce heat and simmer for one hour.

title: country potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Peel and mash with a fork.
Will be lumpy.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well. Press into the bottom of a pan and bake at 350° until lightly browned (burns easily). Cool completely.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat.
Mix together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven, but leave it on.
Spread marshmallows over cake. Return to oven for 20 minutes more or until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from oven.
Cool for 20 minutes, then spread with icing.

title: huiguoi squash
directions: Bake at 375 degrees for 1/2 hour.

title: tuna ball or log
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix with cream cheese.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Roll in a ball or a log.
Roll in nuts.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: baker's clay
directions: Mix with hands and knead for 6 minutes. Add more flour, if too sticky. Form shapes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cook dates, 1/4 cup sugar, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and nuts until thick.
Cool.
Cream margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Next, add dry ingredients (flour, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt).

title: perfect prime rib roast
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first four ingredients; rub over the roast. Place in a large resealable plastic bag; seal and refrigerate overnight, turning often.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients with a mixer.
Pour into pastry filled pie tins.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and reduce the heat to 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes three 9-inch pies.

title: healthy tuna salad
directions: Mix together and serve.
Yields 1 cup.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layers of vegetables in order given in crock-pot. Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned beef on top of celery.
Mix tomato soup with water and pour into crock-pot.
Cover and set on low for 6 to 8 hours (high for 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally).

title: spinach casserole
directions: Squeeze liquid from spinach. Combine all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour into a bowl and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: great gravy
directions: Combine flour, Lawry's seasoning, garlic powder, pepper, and 1/2 cup water to make a non-lumpy paste.
Add more water to get the lumps out if needed.
Slowly add paste to remaining liquids.
Stir constantly in medium heat until thick.
It may take awhile.
If you increase the heat too much, gravy will get lumpy.

title: quick mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of glass baking dish.
Add can of chili and peppers to taste.
Spread 1/2 of Cheddar cheese. Blend slightly.
Empty rest of Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Be sure top layer of cheese is melted. Dig in.

title: dark sweet fruit cake
directions: In bowl, combine egg and water.
Add remaining ingredients by hand.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pan that is well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° as directed for pan size.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Loosen around edges and remove from pan.
If desired, glaze with warm corn syrup and decorate with candied fruits and nuts.
You can use several different sizes of pan.

Bake in 8 x 4-inch for 70 to 80 minutes, in 9 x 5-inch for 60 to 70 minutes, in 10-inch Bundt or tube pan for double recipe for 65 to 70 to 75 minutes, in ring mold (6 to 8-cup) for 40 to 50 minutes or in muffin pans for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no fat - no sugar rice pudding
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add rice.
Lower heat and cook about 20 minutes or until rice is tender and all water absorbed.
Cool rice completely and then put in fridge until it's cold.
Mix pudding as directed on the package.
Add pudding to cold rice.
Plump the raisins in a little hot water.
Let cool.
Add to rice mixture along with the cinnamon.
Cool until serving time.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Slice each onion about 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings. Soak in cold, salted water about 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine bread crumbs, poultry seasoning and Parmesan cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix egg and water; beat well.
Dip onion rings into bread crumb mixture; then into egg mixture and then into crumbs again.
Salt lightly if desired.
Arrange rings on a greased jelly roll pan.
Cover with foil and bake in a hot 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking 20 minutes more or until crispy.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Bread chicken; fry until brown.
Cook broccoli.
Lay chicken on bottom of buttered Pyrex dish, then place cooked broccoli on top of chicken.
Mix together the mayonnaise, soup, broth, lemon juice and milk.
Pour mixture over broccoli, then cover with grated cheese.
Cover completely with breadcrumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ann's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour.
Peel and slice apples.
Toss in dry mixture.
Place apples in pie crust.
Dot the top with butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake for 10 minutes and lower temperature to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Combine honey, orange juice, chili sauce, mustard and browning sauce; stir.
Arrange chicken breasts in 12 x 8-inch dish with meatier portions toward edge of dish.
Pour honey mixture over chicken.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High 7 to 8 minutes and at Medium-low for 8 to 9 minutes or until chicken is done.
Let stand, uncovered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Mix oleo, Sweet 'N Low, eggs, cinnamon and allspice.
Stir in applesauce, flour, soda and vanilla.
Beat at low speed.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° until done.

title: bunny's best dessert
directions: *May substitute any flavor pudding.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook the egg, dates, sugar and butter for 10 minutes over low heat.
Cool, then add the Rice Krispies, vanilla and nuts.
Shape into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll balls in coconut.
Good at Christmastime.

title: frozen fruit pie(club member: lee ann mcraney)
directions: Add sugar to whipping cream. Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add pineapple (juice and all), cherries and nuts. Layer with vanilla wafers and freeze.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar; add milk.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased glass baking dish.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Cook all ingredients for 20 minutes.
Puree in blender. Garnish with chives.

title: banana split ice cream cake
directions: In blender crumb cookies.
Add margarine and put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Press flat.
Put in freezer until chilled.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in saucepan.
Heat to boiling and cook 3 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Do not drain.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in raisins and liquid.
Add flour mixture gradually.
Stir in nuts. Drop by tablespoonfuls about 1 inch apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toast almonds in a dry skillet until light brown, stirring frequently.
Mix all ingredients.
Layer with lettuce on bread for sandwiches.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light.
Add beaten eggs and whip into the mixture. Add flour mixture and bananas alternately, beating smooth after each addition.
Turn into greased and floured 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: eclair cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Place one layer of crackers in the bottom of pan. Pour 1/2 of the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Repeat the layers, ending with a layer of crackers.
Microwave the icing for 30 seconds and spread over the crackers.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: potatoes and pasta(patata e pasta)
directions: In medium saucepan heat
oil and brown garlic.
Pour in tomatoes, tomato sauce, parsley,
salt
and
pepper.
Let cook for 3 to 4 minutes; then
add 1-inch cubed potatoes.
Stir for a few minutes.
Watch
so potatoes don't stick.
Add 10 ounces water and cook
on
medium-low heat until potatoes are tender. Cook pasta shells
or spaghetti, broken into 1-inch pieces and cooked according
to
package
directions.
Combine
pasta and potatoes together and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: water chestnuts with bacon
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until almost crisp.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts and secure with toothpick.
Place in baking dish.
Mix Miracle Whip, brown sugar and chili sauce.
Pour over water chestnuts.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and creamy mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Yields six dozen cookies.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix together. Combine and add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight. Drain before serving.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Whisk egg whites until frothy.
Whisk in maple syrup, juice and milk.
Add spices and zest.
Whisk to blend.
Stir in oats, flour and powder with wooden spoon.
Fold in the rest.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes until firm in center.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put all ingredients except oatmeal into a bowl.
Beat all together with a mixer.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pineapple-lime salad
directions: Mix jello; set until slightly firm, then mix remaining ingredients.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt margarine and add to graham cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press into spring mold 10-inch pan.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Combine onion and celery with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Or use 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute or more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Coconut is optional.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: meat loaf pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly mix bread, meat, milk, egg, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Spread mixture evenly in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain fat from meat loaf.
Pile mashed potatoes on meat loaf as for meringue on pie.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes and bake until cheese is melted.

title: finger gelatin
directions: Add unflavored gelatine to cold water and let stand.
Put hot water, sugar and jello in a pan and heat, stirring, until it boils. Mix with first mixture and stir until all the gelatine dissolves. Add the ice water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil 5 chicken breasts until tender.
Remove meat from bone. Brown 1 medium onion in butter.
In greased casserole dish, put chicken, onion and 1 cup cooked rice.
Pour 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 cup chicken broth over ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together with hands and roll into marble balls.
Bake at 370° for about 10 minutes.

title: onion-cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onion in small amount of hot butter until tender, but not brown. Combine egg and milk. Add to biscuit mix. Stir only until mix is just moistened.
Add onion, half the cheese and parsley. Spread dough into greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle melted butter over top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in large skillet.
Add wild rice and white rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, about 5 minutes. Add broth and mushrooms; bring to a boil.
Pour in greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
This does become dry, but it can be fluffed up by lightly stirring with spoon.
Serves 6.

title: mexican enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Line 8 x 6-inch pan with tortillas.
Pour in meat.
Add beans, sauce and soup.
Top with cheese and another layer of tortillas.
Pour tomatoes and chilies over the top.
Bake an hour at 350° and cool.
Freezes well.
It is really good to tear up large pieces of chips and put some on each serving; makes it more crisp.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix ingredients well. Cook at 350° until done. Bake in oblong pan.

title: light and airy dessert
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add drained fruit.
Add eggs, flour and sugar to fruit juice.
Cook until thickened.
Add to noodles and fruit.
Chill overnight.
Mix with Cool Whip before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and chopped onion for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine mushroom soup and sour cream.
Add raw shredded carrots.
Mix gently with zucchini/onion mixture.
Combine separately stuffing mix and softened margarine.

title: "ginger snappy"
directions: Stir well until blended.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight. Serve as a dip or on crackers.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer onion, broccoli and water for 10 minutes.
Add beef or chicken bouillon cube and milk thickened with flour.
Simmer (do not boil).
Just before serving, add Velveeta cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir enough to melt cheese.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: greek chicken oregano
directions: Turn oven to 500°.
Rinse and drain chicken.
Mix oregano, salt and pepper.
Rub on both sides of chicken.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Whisk oil and lemon juice; pour half over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes, turn, pour remaining oil-lemon juice on chicken and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Preheat oven.
Generously grease muffin pans.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
With a pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
In a small bowl, stir yogurt until cream.
Blend in eggs and vanilla, pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir until flour is just moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven (don't burn!).
Serve warm.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, beat in eggs, sugar and oil.
Add other ingredients and pour into well-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes.
A very moist cake that freezes well.

title: monkey bread
