directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix with sugar and cinnamon. Put into greased Bundt pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 15 minutes in preheated oven.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs well.
Alternate dry ingredients with vanilla, ending with dry.
Place large clumps (golf ball size) on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 18 minutes.
Depending on size of clumps, yield is 1 1/2 dozen large cookies.

title: ida's greens
directions: Put pork in a pot with the water.
Add a few grinds of black pepper; bring to a boil, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Taste broth and add additional pepper and salt if needed.

title: golden yam rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine shortening, milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl; stir until shortening melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°. Add yams, egg and yeast mixture, mixing well.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: honey mustard sauce for chicken
directions: Melt margarine and mix together with rest of ingredients.
Can bake chicken in this and baste every 15 to 30 minutes or use like barbecue sauce on the grill.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Beat
margarine
and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Stir in blueberries, coated
with
extra
2 teaspoons sugar and 1 teaspoon plain flour.
Bake 70 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer or by hand.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover pan lightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and remove foil cover after 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Cut into finger size squares. Coat with potato starch.

title: taco soup
directions: Simmer ingredients until flavors are blended.
Put in bowls. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of soup.

title: brownies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and eggs.
Sift in flour and cocoa.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tijuana taco dip
directions: Stir together beans, 3 tablespoons of tomato sauce and 1/2 teaspoon red pepper sauce and spread in a 1 1/2 quart baking dish. Top with tomatoes, shredded Jack cheese.
Add chili powder to beef and cook until brown and drain.
Add remaining tomato sauce, salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper sauce.
Spread over casserole. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Mix lightly and put into greased and floured pie pan or 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned or apples are done, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Marinate for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hopi fry bread(wequivi)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually stir in water to make a soft dough.
Continue stirring until dough is smooth and shiny.
Cover bowl with a clean towel and set aside for 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 16 balls, about the size of an egg and roll them on a lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness or less.
Pour oil 1 1/2-inch deep in a heavy frying pan and heat until it is just before the smoking point.
Place dough into hot oil, turning with a fork when it has browned on 1 side, until it is golden brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients by hand.
Make well in center of dry ingredients and pour liquid mixture; stir until well mixed.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pans.
Use 6 (3 x 6 x 2-inch) pans or 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for large loaves and 40 minutes for small pans.
Real good sliced thin and spread with cream cheese.

title: impossible coconut pie *
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch pie pans.
Beat all ingredients, except coconut.
Pour into the two shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: leona's chewies
directions: Put box of brown sugar in top of double boiler with simmering water.
Mix together the next 5 ingredients and stir into brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased pan and bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into squares while warm.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: jalapeno roll-ups
directions: In food processor or blender, chop peppers, then nuts.
Add cheese.
Roll up 1 full teaspoon of cheese mix in each ham slice.

title: cherry 'n apple dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9-inch square baking dish, combine pie filling, apples and ReaLemon.
In bowl, cut margarine into cake mix until crumbly.
Add pecans.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: pickled beets
directions: Peel raw beets. Cook until tender. Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Add cooked beets.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack beets into canning jars.
Pour syrup over beets. Seal. Yields about 4 pints.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream together sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Fold in pineapple and bread cubes.
Bake in 8 x 13-inch greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: linda's tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Boil in a large pot the zucchini, onion and next 6 ingredients. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until zucchini are tender.
Spoon soup into bowls and top with cheese. Serve with chips.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cool whip fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and fold all ingredients into Cool Whip. Refrigerate until serving time, placing a cherry on top of each serving, if desired.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Mix cooked noodles, peas and corn together with mushroom soup and sour cream.
Put all in casserole. Brown bread crumbs in butter and spread on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: First cook macaroni (rinse and drain).
Set aside until later. In large skillet, add hamburger and onion; brown until cooked.
Add tomatoes.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar or more to taste.
Simmer these ingredients for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add your cooked macaroni to meat and tomato mixture.
Add salt and pepper, also grated cheese on it, too.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour part of mix into jello mold.
Freeze overnight.
Just before serving, unmold frozen juice and place in punch to keep cold.

title: oatmeal piemocha nut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean (about 50 minutes).

title: fast fixin chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan.
Stir with fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides.
Spread batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean. Sprinkle cooled cake with powdered sugar.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cream together Sugar and Butter.
Add Eggs and beat.
Add Flour, Nuts and Apricots.
LAST add Milk (with sifted ingredients in it).
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pan at 325 for 1 hour.

title: sholezard(saffron-flavored rice pudding)
directions: Bring rice, butter and salt to a boil in water; cover and simmer gently until rice is soft and swollen, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking, about 45 minutes.
Add sugar and lemon juice to rice mixture and mash with potato masher.
Add cardamon. Dissolve saffron in hot water; add to rice mixture.
Mix well. Pour pudding in large serving bowl.
Decorate top with cinnamon and almonds.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients;
pour
into 2 unbaked pie shells. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven baby back ribs
directions: Cut ribs into 3 to 4 rib sections and season with Cavender's seasoning, pepper and paprika.
Place ribs, bone side down, in shallow roasting pan.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May be done to this point and refrigerated.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and sausage.
Pour in baking dish (2 1/2-quart) with 1/4 cup milk.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over sausage mix.
Place cheese on top.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: summertime choco-cream tart
directions: Prepare Pecan Crust; cool completely on wire rack.
In large microwave-safe bowl, stir together whipping cream and sugar. Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or just until mixture begins to boil.
Stir in chocolate chunks until chunks are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Refrigerate until mixture is completely cool and thickened slightly.
Beat just until mixture stiffens and lightens in color; spread evenly over cooled crust.
Cover; refrigerate until firm.
Spread with whipped topping; garnish with fresh fruit.
Serve cold. Refrigerate leftover dessert.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and chop very fine.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter and oil.
In a bowl, combine seasonings, bread crumbs and cheese; add mushroom mixture and stir until thoroughly moistened.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cleaned chops (single layer) in a shallow baking pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
On each chop, place onion slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.
Watch that chops don't dry out.
Add water to pan as necessary.
Baste as needed.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon in small bowl for topping; reserve.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture and beat just until thoroughly combined.
Pour half the batter in a greased tube pan.
Cover with the reserved topping. Pour in remaining batter over topping.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 large coffee cake.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Dip is done when it bubbles on top.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.

title: herbed corn-on-the-cob
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Cut four large squares of foil. Peel back but do not remove the corn husks.
Remove the corn silk. In a small bowl, blend together the butter, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of herbed butter on each ear of corn, then close the husk around the corn.
Wrap each ear of corn tightly in foil and bake for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: oh henry! bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oats, syrup and vanilla.
Pat dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (no longer!).

title: almond english toffee
directions: Mix ingredients, except almonds.
Cook to 295°, stirring constantly.
Stir in almonds.
Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet. Working quickly, spread as thinly as possible.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and spread on the cooled toffee.
Put in a cool place to harden and then turn over and spread chocolate on other side.
Cool until firm.
Break into desired pieces.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients (drain artichokes and chop into large pieces).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers, Melba toast or Doritos.

title: macaroni-cheese-beef casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to package directions. Set aside. Brown ground beef in a skillet, stirring until it crumbles. Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Combine macaroni and cheese dinner, beef and tomatoes in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 5 additional minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread chicken over broccoli.
Place (1/8-inch thick) slices of cheese over chicken.
Mix soup and Miracle Whip together and spread over cheese. Sprinkle water chestnuts on top.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove from oven and cover with French fried onions. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: candied pork chops
directions: Spread 1 cup brown sugar in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup ketchup and 1/8 cup lemon juice over brown sugar and mix together.
Place pork chops on top.
Put remaining brown sugar, ketchup and lemon juice (mixed) over pork chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, turning once after 45 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, turn oven up to 425° and cover with foil to candy pork chops.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick oleo.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick oleo; add eggs, 1 at a time and beat after each.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Add melted candy and oleo to mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: low-fat nachos
directions: Place chips, cheese and refried beans on plate and microwave until warm.
Place other ingredients on top.
Use other low or no-fat toppings, if desired.
May cut this down for 1 serving or increase the amount for more people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli using package directions; drain. Combine broccoli, mayonnaise, soup, onion and egg in bowl. Mix well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: hot sausage(great for a crowd!)
directions: Brown peppers, onions and sausage in a skillet.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Add sausage, onions and peppers.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve on semi-hard rolls.

title: pumpkin pie for diabetics
directions: Beat eggs
and
add
in
order
with 1/4 teaspoon salt, Sucaryl solution, melted butter, hot pumpkin and scalded milk. Pour into
chilled
unbaked
pie shell and bake.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni/noodles with chopped up onion.
Drain and mix with all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover top with crushed up potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes in oven on 300°, or bake for 15 minutes in microwave.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove bones from chicken. Cut in small pieces.
Mix rice, chicken soup and onion.
Use water chestnuts and almonds, if desired.
Just as good without.
Place cracker crumbs on top and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix both sugars, cornmeal, flour, eggs butter and milk together.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Mix orange cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into a 13 x 9 pan and bake according to directions.
After removing cake from oven, poke holes in cake (1-inch apart) with a fork.

title: * leroy's trout *
directions: Clean trout and roll in dry ingredients, which you can mix well.
Insert 1/2 slice bacon in cavity of trout and fry until done in equal parts butter or margarine and shortening.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and cool sausage; beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and dry mustard, beat again.
Add bread (make into crumbs first) and stir. Add cheese, sausage, mushrooms and stir.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in milk. Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture with milk.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill.
Drop small bits of dough on greased baking sheets and bake 20 minutes at 275°.
If desired, add a pecan or cherry half to top of each cookie.

title: tomatoes and okra
directions: Cook okra according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook onion and green pepper in oil until tender, but not brown.
Blend in sugar, flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and okra.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are hot through, stirring as little as possible.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple baked beans
directions: Mix beans and brown sugar to taste.
Cut up pineapple in mixture and stir in salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish. Put strips of bacon on top.
Bake until strips of bacon are brown in a 350° oven.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Mix in the peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: quick pickled cucumbers
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish, stir together vinegar, sugar, salt and crushed red pepper. Cut each unpeeled cucumber lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Place in baking dish with marinade. Peel carrot and cut crosswise in half. Cut each half lengthwise into matchstick thin strips.
Place carrots in baking dish with cucumbers. Toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 16 accompaniment servings.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and banana and mix well.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch bread pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean from center.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Wrap loaf in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a wide mouthed bottle and shake. Chill.
Shake and mix thoroughly before serving.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and let cool.
Mix other ingredients together. Mix in shortening.
Chill in refrigerator a short time.
Make 1-inch balls and roll in sugar (small cookies) or make large balls, flatten and press into sugar (large cookies).
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes for small cookies and 10 to 14 minutes for large cookies.
Don't overbake!!
They don't look done when you take them out of oven.
Allow cookies to cool or they break apart when removing from pan.
But don't let them cool completely before removing.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter
and sugar together.
Add the egg yolk and vanilla, blending well.
Blend in the flour, little at a time. Fold in
the
crushed
chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: victory cake(an easy make cake)
directions: Combine raisins, sugar, water, shortening and spices.
Heat to boiling and simmer 2 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Resift flour with soda and salt.
Stir into raisin mixture along with nuts.
Turn into greased 9-inch tube or square pan.
Bake in slow (300°) oven 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: seafood salad
directions: Dice crab meat into small chunks.
Add onions, blades and celery together.
Add mayonnaise and black pepper to taste. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix together and spread on crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and flour.
Press dough in greased pan and add apples on top of dough.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo. Add egg. Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll and cut with glass.
Fill with apricot or raisins.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fried squirrel(nikw-abenaki)
directions: Cut squirrel into serving pieces and shake in paper bag containing flour and seasonings to dredge well.
Fry in skillet until brown.
Remove meat from skillet and pour off all grease except 2 tablespoons.
Add water and bring to boil.
Return squirrel to skillet; reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook for about 1 hour until meat falls off bone.

title: hot mexi dip
directions: In a large skillet brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add ground beef and refried beans together.
Mix well.
Add picante sauce.
Heat until hot, then add 1 large package of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Dip with tortilla chips.
Enjoy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oil.
Boil squash until tender. Pour off water.
Add egg and milk, after mixing together.
Add also the cracker crumbs and 1 cup cheese.
Pour into a baking dish.
Put 1/2 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: low-fat party mix
directions: In a large baking pan, combine first 7 ingredients.
As you add each cereal, spray very lightly with a vegetable spray.
This will help the cereal mixture absorb the seasonings.
Stir.
Combine the 2 sauces and liquid smoke.
Sprinkle over cereal mixture, stir often.
Combine remaining 5 ingredients and sprinkle over party mix, stirring several times.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk; crush with hands until well mixed.
Then add eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Stir well.
Pour oleo in bottom of thick pan and bake until firm.
Let cool, then cube pudding and put in individual dessert dishes.
When ready to serve, add Whiskey Sauce and heat under broiler.

title: fettucine fragale
directions: Combine 1/4 cup butter, parsley and basil; blend in Ricotta, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and blend well; keep warm.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Cook garlic in 1/2 cup butter for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over noodles; toss lightly and quickly. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese; toss again.
Pile noodles on warm platter and spoon sauce over; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Melt cheese and margarine in double boiler.
Layer broccoli and crackers in casserole dish.
Pour cheese over broccoli and crackers.
Bake at 320° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, except oatmeal. Mix raisins

and nuts with small amount of flour mixture. Cream shortening, add sugar, well beaten egg and milk. Add gradually the dry ingredients, add oatmeal, nuts and raisins. Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven 350°-375° for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: k's skillet vegies
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add peppers and onions and saute until tender.
Add olives, mushrooms and pineapple and simmer until heated through.
Can add celery with peppers and onion, if desired.
Very good with steak.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
In large skillet, saute celery and onions until soft; add flour to thicken.
Add milk to make a sauce.
Add Velveeta.
After Velveeta is melted, add chilies and chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: dill pickles
directions: This makes liquid for 2 quarts pickles.
Pour hot liquid over pickles in jar and seal.

title: easy eggplant parmigiana
directions: Place eggplant slices on greased broiler pan.
Brush with some of the oil.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes. Turn slices; brush with remaining oil.
Broil 4 minutes more. Combine spaghetti sauce, onion, garlic and salt.
Spread each slice with some spaghetti sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Top each with 3 thin strips of Mozzarella.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes more or until lightly browned and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put ingredients in blender in order given.
Cover and run at high speed until well blended.
Chill.
Serve as dip with crackers or potato chips.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in a greased skillet. Add tomatoes, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Cook macaroni in salted water; drain.
Add to ingredients in skillet.
Let simmer until blended well.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; pick off the bones.
Cut up in small pieces. Cook noodles in the broth that the chicken was cooked in.
Mix all ingredients together; add salt and pepper to taste.
Put into a baking dish; cover with bread crumbs and pour melted butter over top.
Put as many crumbs as you like.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend.
Better when made ahead.
Keeps well.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a frying pan.
Add mushrooms. Cover and saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over butter-mushroom mixture, stirring thoroughly to blend.
Add milk slowly.
Continue to stir.
Then add cream and salt and raise heat slighlty.
Cook until thickened, stirring to keep smooth.
Good to serve over meats, chicken or fish.

title: scallops in white wine
directions: In saucepan, heat oil, garlic and all seasonings.
Add water and wine.
Add scallops.
Cover and simmer over low flame for 20 minutes.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Dissolve jello gelatin and salt in boiling water.
In pot, add butter and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add sweet potatoes and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, basting frequently.
When syrup thickens and is glossy, remove from heat.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Combine ingredients in a large roaster or casserole; cover. Cook 5 hours at 250°.
Never remove lid while cooking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cucumber gelatin
directions: Dissolve jello in cup of hot water.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise, horseradish and salt.
Blend with beater until smooth. Add lemon juice.
Chill until partly set.
Stir in cucumber and onion.
Turn into 3-cup mold and chill until firm.

title: spinach-bacon deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in half lengthwise, scoop out yolks into small mixing bowl and mash well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato soup and water.
Form into balls.
Place in baking dish and mix soup and water and pour over meat balls.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashion apple cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (flour, spices and baking soda). In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla well.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and chips.
Pour in a tube pan (greased and floured) and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples and water, layered, in a 10 x 6-inch baking pan. Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt into a bowl.
Cut in margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together carrots, sugar, cooking oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed ingredients; stir in nuts.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: creamy orange mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted and smooth.
Stir in orange juice.
Pour into a 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold. Garnish with orange slices and strawberries, if desired.

title: chicken lucia
directions: Rub chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in oiled baking dish. Brush with oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, turning once during cooking period.
Remove from oven.

title: colleen's lime jello
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water mix well, add cold water and mix. Place in refrigerator for 1 hour until just starting to set. Once Jello is ready, mix remaining ingredients into Jello with electric mixer on medium speed.
Place in a 9 x 12 inch or 9 x 13 inch dish and refrigerate until firm.
Enjoy!

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, melted margarine and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir several times while baking.
Cool; spread 2/3 of the crumb mixture in the pan.

title: green chili stew
directions: Boil meat until tender. Grind or pull apart in strings as coarse as possible. Add other ingredients to water that is left from roast. Simmer until onions are tender. Serve with tortillas.

title: banana orange smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.

title: caramels
directions: Boil the sugar, syrup, water and vinegar for 6 minutes.
Add the butter.
Cool until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from fire; stir in vanilla.
Turn into buttered tins.
Mark in squares when cool; cut when cold.
Recipe is from Nettie (Crum) Allen.

title: chi-chi's dish
directions: Leave cream cheese out to soften; spread in a pie pan.
Then add Chi-Chi's sauce on top.
Then add cheese to top.
Dip with nacho chips.

title: blueberry breakfast cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Add milk, then flour, baking powder and salt alternately.
Add 1/2 cup or more of blueberries to the batter and 1/2 cup on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 8 x 11-inch pan for about 25 minutes or until done.

title: corned beef quiche
directions: Bake the pie shell at 450° for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven. Reduce temperature to 325°.
Crumble corned beef hash into pie shell.
Top with the cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over hash and cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Cool for 25 minutes before serving.

title: slush
directions: Boil water and sugar together.
Take off heat and put tea bags in.
Allow this to cool, then add the rest of the ingredients and freeze for 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
It will not freeze solid.
Put a scoop or two in a tall glass and fill with 7-Up or sour soda.

title: spicy pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan and place on cake rack.

title: grandaddy's favorite apple crunch
directions: Pour pie filling in bottom of cake pan.
Pour dry cake mix on top of filling.
Melt butter and put over cake mix.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45-50 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take meat off bones and crumble up. Cover bottom of bowl with Doritos.
Put chicken on top.
Mix Ro-Tel, broth, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Repeat and cover with Doritos and
cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup and set aside.
Pat remaining in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: christmas applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir only enough to mix.
Don't beat. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, cider, syrup, butter and salt in a large sauce pan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Turn off heat and remove crystalized sugar from pan with a wet brush. Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes, or until thermometer reads 260° (130° c).
Turn to low heat and add vanilla.
Turn off heat.
When mixture is sufficiently cool, pour over popcorn and peanuts.
Mix well and roll into 3 inch balls. Makes 18.

title: quick sherbet punch
directions: Just before serving, spoon sherbet into punch bowl by heaping tablespoonfuls.
Slowly pour chilled ginger ale over sherbet, stirring gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: square dance cake
directions: Mix nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.

title: favorite sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Add onion. Cook until tender. Blend in flour, seasonings and milk. Keep stirring to thicken. Add cheese. Stir until melted. Add remaining
ingredients. Place in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Top with additional cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples and 1/4 cup sugar in a casserole dish or square baking dish.
Blend all other ingredients and cover apples with mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until apples are done, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream, whipped cream or enjoy plain.

title: honey scotch topping for ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, butter, honey and salt in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to a soft ball stage (234°).
Then stir in an additional 1/3 cup evaporated milk and cook until sauce is thick and smooth (about 3 minutes longer).
Makes about 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Serve hot or cold.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix well. Spread in baking dish. Top with 1/3 cup melted butter and crushed chips. Bake at 350° (uncovered) 45 to 60 minutes.

title: meat loafettes
directions: Set out ingredients, mixing bowl, measuring spoons and cups, fork, muffin tins and pot holders.
Set oven at 450°.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add ground steak, 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/8 teaspoon of pepper, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, chopped onion, bread crumbs and vegetable soup.
Mix lightly with fork. Butter 12 muffin tins.
Spoon meat mixture into muffin cups. Round off tops.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: split pea soup
directions: Fill large pan with water just a couple inches from the top. Add ham to water.
Cook at medium temperature for 4 hours.
Take ham out of broth.
Let cool and then cut up.

title: hot cranapple wassail
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Heat on stove about 10 minutes; do not boil.
Remove cinnamon and cloves when serving.

title: shrimp mold
directions: On low heat, warm tomato soup and add gelatin until dissolved. Then add cream cheese until melted, stirring constantly.
Add rinsed, drained, mashed shrimp, mayonnaise, onion and parsley. Brush jello mold with mayonnaise and after pouring mixture into mold, refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage and cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower as directed; drain.
Brown sausage links as directed.
Remove and keep warm.
In skillet over low heat, melt oleo.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Gradually stir in milk and continue cooking, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and Worcestershire sauce, stirring, until cheese melts.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix crumbs, dates, nuts, sugar and salt.
Fold into beaten egg whites.
Add extract.
Spread in a greased pie pie.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg and molasses.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour.
Roll in 1-inch balls, then roll in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and press with damp fork.
Bake for 10 minutes or until slightly brown at 350°. Do not overbake.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies in a 9 x 13-inch container.
Prepare instant vanilla pudding as directed on boxes.
Pour over cookies. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients until it boils and let cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix creamed corn and whole kernel corn with 1 egg and Jiffy corn meal mix.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Pour recipe on melted butter.
Dot with sour cream on top of ingredients. Sprinkle with grated cheese (Cheddar).
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and bubbly (approximately 40 minutes).

title: crunchy cheese dip
directions: Combine all but juice, mix well, then stir in juice (reserved from pineapple).
Mix well, cover and chill.
Serve with crackers. Yields 3 cups.

title: sad cookies
directions: Beat eggs a little; add brown sugar.
Beat until mixed (do not overbeat).
Add Bisquick mix into which nuts and coconut have been added.
Beat just until mixed (do not use mixer).
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes at 325°.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add apples.
Spoon into greased 8-inch square pan.
Mix oatmeal and flour and sprinkle over apple mix.
Melt butter or oleo and drizzle over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sauteed apples
directions: Mix cider, sugar and cinnamon until sugar dissolves. Melt margarine over medium high heat in a 12-inch nonstick skillet. Add apples and stir to coat. Add 1/2 cup cider mixture. Raise heat to high. Cook apples stirring frequently until most liquid has evaporated and begins to burn. Lower heat, add remaining cider mixture. Cook until apples are done and liquid has evaporated, stirring frequently. Serves 4.

title: jiffy pineapple dessert
directions: Gradually add milk to softened cream cheese and blend.
Add instant pudding mix to cheese mixture.
Blend well and refrigerate to thicken.
Drain pineapple.
Let stand as you bake yellow cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes or less.
When cake is cool, spread with vanilla-cheese pudding.
Sprinkle drained pineapple over pudding.
Top with topping of your desire. Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: savannah shrimp paste
directions: Finely chop shrimp in a food processor.
Add other ingredients, except salt and pepper.
Process until smooth. Season to taste.
Pack into a small bowl or crock.
Serve with crackers or toast.

title: cream filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Set aside.
Cream together egg, sugar and cream cheese with mixer.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Fill cupcake liners 1/2 full with cake mix.
Drop a teaspoon of filling in each.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion and green pepper. Drain. Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Spread rice in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Top with sausage mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. (Easily made up night before and refrigerated overnight before baking.)

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add water and chicken bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
When boiling, add broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is tender.

title: chocolate in-betweens
directions: Cream sugar, butter and salt.
Add flour and oats until crumbles.
Press about 2/3 cup mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: salmon on half shell
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut in half and scoop out insides.
Mash with next 7 ingredients until smooth.
Refill potato shells without pressing down.
Sprinkle with fried onions, bacon bits or cheese if desired.
Brown in 450° oven about 10 minutes.
Serve with salad or vegetable.

title: easy hot dogs
directions: Warm the hot dogs so they are easy to split. Place on greased pan. Put mustard, onion and then fill with mashed potatoes. Place a slice of American cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shish kebabs
directions: Marinate shark and vegetables in soy sauce.
Cube shark and quarter vegetables.
Place on skewers, alternating vegetables and shark.
Place on grill covered with Reynolds Wrap and grill 5 minutes on each side.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins, including the area between the cavities.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in egg.
Quickly fold in buttermilk; do not overmix or batter will curdle.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a baking dish large enough to hold apples in a shallow layer.
Mix the salt, flour, cinnamon and sugar; work in butter. Mixture will be fairly crumbly.
Distribute flour-sugar mixture over the top of apples.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes, or until apples are done and crust is brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Slow cook chicken breasts in crock-pot, marinating occasionally with soy sauce.
Cut up chicken when done in small squares.
Quickly fry in oil raw veggies until tender but crunchy. Add water chestnuts, stir quickly for about 15 seconds.
Remove from wok or frypan.
Add chicken to veggies and pour over prepared rice or pasta.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Can also add bean sprouts, zucchini or almonds if your family allows it.

title: sweet corn tomalito
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Cream softened butter together with sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Add milk and masa and mix well.
Use a blender or food processor to puree 2 cups of corn until smooth.
Add pureed corn to butter/masa mixture and mix well.
Add corn meal, baking powder, salt and remaining corn and mix until combined.
Pour mixture into an ungreased 8 X 8 inch baking pan.
Cover with foil and place it into a 9 X 13 inch baking pan.
Add hot water to the larger baking pan until it's about 1/3 full.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until corn cake is firm in the center.
Let it sit covered for 10 minutes before serving.
To serve, scoop out about a 1/2 cup portion with a large spoon.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour half of mixture into a large bowl; let gel.
Top with Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator until set.
Put remaining half of mixture on top of Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator.

title: delicious chop suey
directions: Place meat in large kettle and fry.
Sprinkle with soy sauce. Cover and brown meat.
Add 4 to 6 cups of water and tomato sauce. Wash and drain sprouts and chestnuts.
Add to meat with all other ingredients.
Cook 2 hours.
When celery is tender, thicken with cornstarch.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in double boiler with already rapidly boiling water.
Beat constantly at medium speed. Cook 7 minutes until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla; beat at high speed until thick enough to spread.
Covers two layer 9-inch cake.

title: chicken creole
directions: Puree one can of tomatoes.
Chop remaining can of tomatoes. In skillet combine tomatoes and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chicken and sausage.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cold oven walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco together.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add milk alternating with flour.
Add walnuts that have been blended.
Beat for 8 to 10 minutes at high speed.
Put in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut buttered bread into cubes and place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook sausage, drain and spread over bread cubes. Place grated cheese on top of sausage.
Beat eggs and add half and half.
Pour this over cheese.
Let set overnight.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Chop black walnuts.
Add 1/3 cup flour from the previously measured flour.
Work flour into nuts.
Add alternately the flour with salt added and milk to the creamed mixture.
Then add black walnut flavoring.
Stir in the floured nuts last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: super yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening in milk; add eggs, sugar, salt, water and yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup water and flour.
Knead and let rise. Make into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. If used for dinner rolls, omit 1/4 cup sugar.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour on top of potatoes.
Top with crushed flakes and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: juanita's 3-day slaw
directions: Shred cabbage into large plastic bowl.
Place onions and peppers on top.
Sprinkle sugar over all.
DO NOT STIR!!!
Put rest of ingredients into a saucepan and bring to full boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
AGAIN,
DO NOT STIR!!!
Cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
(This can remain saturating for 3 days in fridge.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in bottom of a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.

title: avocado sauce(ninfa's)
directions: Peel avocado and mash to a smooth pulp.
Add sour cream, milk, onion, garlic, cilantro, pepper sauce and lemon juice.
Blend with wire whisk or in a blender.
Let stand at least an hour before serving.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Leave whites for top (beaten), then bake like any meringue.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Saute mushrooms, carrot and onion in butter in a large skillet over medium heat until tender; drain and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and next 5 ingredients.
Stir well and set aside. Combine spaghetti sauce and tomato paste; stir well.
Spread half of spaghetti sauce mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange 3 lasagna noodles over sauce.
Spread reserved vegetable mixture over noodles.
Spoon half of reserved cottage cheese mixture over vegetable mixture.
Arrange remaining 3 lasagna noodles over cottage cheese mixture and top with remaining sauce mixture, spinach, remaining cottage cheese mixture and chopped tomato.
To store, cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
To serve, bake, covered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese; bake 15 minutes or until lasagna is thoroughly heated and cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli or peas in casserole dish.
Combine mayo, lemon juice and soup; pour over chicken.
Melt butter, pour over bread crumbs and toss well.
Spread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese bites
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into a long roll. Put mixture on wax paper and place in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into slices. Place on cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes in a preheated oven at 325°.

title: ozark cauliflower salad
directions: Boil cauliflower 5 minutes; cool immediately in ice water. Place in bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly; chill and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the all-purpose flour and baking powder.
Cut in the margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in the sour cream and skim milk.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough 8 to 10 times. Roll or pat 1/2-inch thickness.
With 2-inch biscuit cutter, cut dough into 12 circles.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Test for doneness. Simplicity becomes spectacular.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine cake mix, topping and eggs in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.
Place 1/2-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli; add bacon and onions.
In small bowl, mix sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and sunflower seeds.
Pour over broccoli mixture; toss.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: fudgsicles
directions: You will need 3 ounce paper cups and wooden sticks.

title: early colonial bread
directions: Thoroughly combine corn meal, brown sugar, salt, boiling water and oil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Stir into corn meal mixture.
Add whole wheat and rye flour.
Mix well.
Stir in all purpose flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Knead.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to box directions.
When cooked, break half of brownies into bite-size pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare mousse according to package directions and spread half on top of broken brownies.
Crumble 4 candy bars on top of mousse.
Repeat once more, then top with Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together thoroughly sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in sour milk or buttermilk and bananas.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Pour in loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple dump dessert
directions: Pour undrained apples into casserole.
Layer pineapple, cake mix and pecans over apples.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not use pie filling in this recipe.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Chill.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: nana's peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in a deep casserole dish at 350 degrees. Mix sugar, flour and milk into a batter and pour into hot melted butter. Spoon peaches over batter evenly. Pour peach juice over peaches gently. Bake at 350 degrees for an hour or until golden brown. Cinnamon can be added to cobbler. Also sugar and cinnamon can be sprinkled over it before baking. Other fruits can be used in this recipe.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Add vanilla, currants and apples.
Dough will be thick.
Turn into a greased 9 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
While cake is still hot, use a kitchen fork and poke holes in entire cake, so frosting will run in it.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 2 x 1/4 x 1/4-inch strips or cubes.
Coat 6 to 8 strips at a time in mixture of 1/2 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Melt butter in skillet; add meat and onion. Brown slowly.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes. Drain and mash. Add ingredients. Pour into greased casserole. Dot with butter.
Can be refrigerated up to 2 to 3 days. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly combine zucchini, baking soda, sugar, margarine and beaten egg. Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix. Chill at least 2 hours. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: fried catfish
directions: Spread catfish with a thin coating of mustard.
Combine cornmeal, salt, pepper and red pepper in a plastic bag.
Add fish and shake to coat.
Heat cooking oil to 375° in a deep 12-inch skillet.
Fry fillets, two at a time, until fish is golden brown, about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cake frosting
directions: Cook and stir milk and flour until thick.
Set aside to cool. Cream margarine and add sugar; beat until very light and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Add milk and flour mixture and beat.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix until consistency of peas.
Beat one egg and add 1 teaspoon of vinegar.
Add enough cold water to make 1/2 cup of liquid.
Add to flour mixture.
Roll out with alot of flour. Makes 2 crusts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain.
Rinse off with warm water. Cook egg noodles until done.
Open corn; drain water off.
Put corn into same skillet you cooked the ground beef in.
Add tomato sauce.
Put ground beef back into the corn mixture.
Stir until bubbly.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic in bacon drippings.
Add spinach, broth, beans and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Add tortellini; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add remaining crumbled bacon and pepper.
Cook a few minutes and serve.

title: easy vanilla fruit brule
directions: Arrange 10
vanilla
wafers around sides of 1 1/2 quart serving dish.
Spoon
fruit
in
dish.
Spread
sour
cream or yogurt over fruit; top with remaining vanilla wafers.
Combine brown sugar and melted
margarine.	Spoon over vanilla wafers. Broil 6 inches from heat source for
to	4 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off grease.
Add chopped onion, garlic, celery and green pepper to sausage and simmer until tender.
Wash rice and add to mixture in Pyrex baking dish along with the soup. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheese and bacon puffs
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Spread on crackers (Ritz, Town House, etc.). Broil until bubbly and brown.

title: crab cakes with zucchini squash
directions: Mix well and make into patties.
Roll in flour or cornflake crumbs and fry.

title: chicken gravy
directions: Cook fryer chicken down.
Put grease in a skillet.
Let it get medium hot.
Add flour until all is mixed well and brown.
Pour 1 quart of water in the skillet.
Put over chicken.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
May add more water if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rainbow angel food cake
directions: Mix together angel food cake as directed.
Separate mix into 6 small bowls.
Add one color per bowl.
(Mix red and yellow for orange; red and blue for purple).
Leave some mix in large bowl for white.
Spoon colored cake mix into angel food pan until all colored mix is in pan.
Do not stir.
Bounce pan to remove air bubbles.
Bake as directed on mix box.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Cut biscuits into small pieces, mix with other ingredients and bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Add seasoning mix and water to browned and drained hamburger. Simmer until water is gone.
Toss salad.
Put Fritos on plate. Add salad, cheese and hamburger mixture.
Add Old El Paso Picante Sauce (hot sauce).

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix.
Add graham cracker crumbs until dough is thick.
Bake at 350° for exactly 10 minutes.
Take out while warm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soups, chilies and black olives together.
Take 1/3 out and set aside.
Add chicken to remaining 2/3.
Fill tortillas with some cheese in middle and then chicken mixture on top and roll each tortilla and put in greased baking dish.
After all are rolled, add remaining sauce and cheese evenly over top. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add all spices and tomatoes; heat through. Cover bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish with 1/2 tortillas.
Pour beef mixture over tortillas, place 2nd layer of tortillas over meat mixture.
Combine cheeses and egg; pour over tortillas and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients. Blend all together.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples, walnuts and raisins.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan evenly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole with mushrooms
directions: In a frying pan with a lid or a Dutch oven, bring chicken broth to simmering over medium heat.
Place chicken breasts in a single layer; cover and poach until meat is tender when pierced with a fork (about 15 minutes).
Lift chicken from broth; cool, then remove skin and pull bones from chicken; reserve 3/4 cup of the broth for sauce (save remaining for another use such as soups or broth stews).
In a shallow casserole (about 8 x 12-inches), arrange chicken breast pieces, slightly overlapping; distribute drained artichoke hearts in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: missouri
directions: In a greased casserole, make layers of beef, onions and potatoes.
Mix 1 can tomato soup diluted with about 1/2 can water and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours, until potatoes are done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and break up.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and mayo; pour over salad.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry surpeme
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Put 1/2 aside.
Blend cake mix, eggs, oil, water, gelatin and remainder of strawberries.
Using 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans, greased and floured, bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on racks.

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onion in butter or canola oil until transparent.
Add prepared mustard and cornstarch, then add milk into the mixture. Add approximately 1/3 of grated sharp cheese and mix in salt. Butter or spray with Pam a deep dish baking pan.
Put in layer of macaroni; cover with sauce and sprinkle grated New York sharp cheese and repeat.
Leave enough sauce and cheese for the top. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Reheat any leftovers in microwave. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: midwest meat loaf with cheese sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir Velveeta, milk and mustard in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Reserve 3/4 cup cheese sauce.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup cheese sauce with remaining ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Shape into 8 x 3-inch loaf in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serve with reserved cheese sauce.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together and pour into Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Serve as an ice cream dish.

title: linzer augen cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl; chill for 1 hour.
Remove; shape into large or small marble-size balls in the palm of your hands.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Make a depression in each with your index finger, fill with a bit of thick jam (apricot, plum or raspberry).
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 8 minutes or until delicately browned. Remove from sheet while still warm.
Cool (on racks for best results), then sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight containers; keep in cool place.
Flavor, like people improves with aging!

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Add apples and pecans (more if desired).
Mixture will be very thick and stiff.
Pour and spoon into 10 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: million dollar pickles
directions: Wash and
cube
peppers, onions, cucumbers and carrots. Place all veggies in a large bowl.
Cover with water and 1 cup salt. Let stand at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt into a 2 quart dish.
Place in microwave and bring to a boil.
Cook on full power for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in the baking soda, vanilla and maple flavoring.
Put popcorn in a brown paper bag and pour syrup mixture over the popcorn.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
Tightly close bag and shake well.
Cook in bag on full power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from the microwave and shake. Return to microwave and cook 1 1/2 minutes longer.
Remove and pour over cookie sheet to cool.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream together and chill.
Serve with club crackers.

title: chicken poo(serves 8)
directions: Spread chicken breasts with butter and place in well sealed foil pouches (2 breasts to a pouch) and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool, skin and bone.
Cut in half.
Parboil broccoli; drain and seal with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Saute crumbs. Mix sauce.
The day you serve, put broccoli in casserole; top with chicken breasts.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake 35 minutes in 325° oven.

title: layered squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan, then put in graham cracker crumbs. Pour melted butter over crumbs; pack into bottom of pan, then pour condensed milk over graham cracker crumbs.
Then pour package of chocolate chips on condensed milk, then put on the nuts and top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until coconut browns.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain liquid from dill pickles.
Slice pickles.
Pack in same original jar.
Cover with sugar.
Turn jar upside down several times to mix thoroughly and dissolve sugar.
Place in fridge. Ready to eat in 24 hours.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Use a 3-quart pot.
To the milk, add sugar, pinch of salt and rice; bring to a boil.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Beat egg with cornstarch and vanilla; add 1 1/2 cups of milk and mix well.
Add egg-milk mixture to rice mixture; stir constantly to prevent scorching.
As soon as it thickens some, remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes.
The last addition of milk makes it creamy.

title: microwave egg drop soup
directions: In a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole, combine water, onion, bouillon granules, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Cook, covered, on High (100%) for 7 to 9 minutes or until mixture boils.
Using a circular motion, slowly pour eggs into soup in a thin stream. Cook, uncovered, on High (100%) for 1 minute to finish cooking eggs, stirring once during cooking.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: german pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Brown onions and peppers.
Pour off grease.
Strain tomatoes and add them to chops, onions and peppers.
Simmer with the bay leaves until tender.
Remove the chops and thicken liquid with 1 teaspoon flour.
Use this gravy over chops.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken divan
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Sprinkle salt and paprika over chicken; brown. Remove from pan.
Lay broccoli in single layer in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Spread over chicken. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese over top and broil 2 to 3 minutes until browned.

title: clear beef soup
directions: Mix water, bouillon and soy sauce in 4 cup measure.
Microwave uncovered on High heat (100%) to boiling, 5 to 7 minutes.
Slice mushrooms into 6 small bowls.
Add lemon slices and broth. Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: kid's play dough
directions: Cook in 1 1/2-quart saucepan 4 to 5 minutes over medium heat until mixture forms ball, stirring vigorously.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Knead dough until blended smoothly.
Cool; store in airtight containers.
A few drops of food coloring may be added to dough that has been divided and put in Ziploc bags. Knead dough to blend food coloring.
After using dough, will keep longer in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands and form into ball.
Roll in ground pecans.
Double recipe for parties.

title: mushroom florentine
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Season with salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons butter.
Place spinach in a buttered 10-inch pie pan and
cover with 1/2 pound grated cheese and onions.
Saute mushrooms in
or 4 tablespoons of butter.
Spread on top of spinach
and
cheese.
Cover
the mushrooms with remaining 1/2 pound grated
cheese.
Bake
for
minutes at 350° or until hot.
Serves 8.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix and pour over hot cake.

title: mexican dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
To assemble, spread bean dip on shallow pan.
Top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream and taco mix.
Sprinkle with onion, olives and tomatoes.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: swedish nut cake(very easy, very moist)
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean after inserted. When cool, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Ice and sprinkle with coconut.

title: alaska snow crab dip
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Blend and mix remaining ingredients together. Fold in crabmeat.
Chill until ready to serve, approximately 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: texas tacos
directions: Brown ground beef over medium heat.
Salt to taste while cooking.
Shred lettuce in food processor or with a knife.
Mash cut tomatoes or put into blender until they are small chunks.
Add minced garlic and oregano to tomatoes.
Add salt to taste.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the margarine. Add flour.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and add to flour mixture.
Add milk and simmer. Add Cheez Whiz and Worcestershire sauce and simmer until thickened. Add beer and cook until hot.
Float popcorn on top. May add shredded vegetables and chives.

title: fast and easy macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni in water until tender and drain thoroughly. Stir in butter and eggs.
Mix mustard and egg with 1 tablespoon hot water and add to milk; set aside.
Add cheese to macaroni, reserving enough cheese to spread on top.
Pour into greased casserole.
Add milk; sprinkle with reserved cheese.

title: mexican dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Layer with chips and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
This can be frozen.

title: chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Cook the sugar, water and cream of tartar to 260° or to the hard ball stage, then add the flavors.
Pour a portion of the syrup over the popcorn and let the remainder stand in a warm place.
Form into small popcorn balls then dip them into the remaining syrup, one at a time.
Lay on waxed paper to become firm, then dip in the melted chocolate.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water (no salt).
Remove from bone; cut into bite size pieces.
Melt butter; mix with dressing.
Layer 1/2 of chicken and stuffing.
Pour 1 can of mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 can chicken broth.
Make another layer of chicken and stuffing.
Pour 1 can of mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 can of chicken broth.
Sprinkle dry stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Shake well.
Chill. Do not use blender.
Add Blue cheese when ready to serve.
Best on romaine/leaf lettuce.

title: peach ice cream(low calorie)
directions: Chop enough peaches to make 1 Cup.
Puree remaining peaches in blender or food processor to measure 2 1/2 cups.
Sprinkle gelatin over milk in medium saucepan.
Let stand one minute to soften.

title: done buttered biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick and sour cream.
Add margarine and mix well. Fill greased mini-muffin tins. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Melt margarine; saut onions in butter or margarine.
Brown the hamburger; stir in chili powder and dash of salt to taste. Add tomatoes, squashed by hand.
Add kidney beans, water and tomato catsup.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: oven barbecued swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat steak and brown in hot oil in ovenproof Dutch oven.
Break up canned tomatoes and mix remaining ingredients except onion.
Pour over steak; add salt and pepper if needed and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add onion; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with hot noodles or rice.

title: sweet fritters
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat just until free of lumps.
Use fresh or canned fruit, washed and dried. Dust each piece of fruit with flour; slip in batter and fry in 2 to 3 inches hot oil at 375° until golden brown on both sides, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: tomato cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: seashell-pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours before serving. (I think it's better when made a day ahead of time.)
Makes 10 cups of salad.

title: tangy cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans.
Mix well. Chill overnight.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown the chopped onion with the 1/2 stick of margarine.
Add chicken soup and milk, mixed together.
Add grated Cheddar cheese; add salt.
Combine this mixture with the hash brown potatoes; stir together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes stirred in melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Next add melted butter. Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baking chip cookies
directions: Beat
shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs until light and
fluffy.
Mix
flour
with soda and salt in separate bowl, then
blend
in
shortening
mixture.
Stir
in nuts and chips. Drop
2-inches apart from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake
in
preheated
375° oven for about 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown the hamburger. Saute the green pepper and onion. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, garlic, mustard, pepper, parsley and cilantro. Spread paprika and nuts on wax paper.
Roll cheese ball in nuts and paprika and refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; put in casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup and milk; mix well.
Fold in 3/4 of the onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle the rest of the onion rings on top; put back in oven until browned (approximately 10 minutes).

title: potato bacon chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until the fat becomes transparent, being careful not to overcook.
Add potatoes and onions.
Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender (about 15 to 20 minutes). Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring frequently, until heated through.

title: peanut pie
directions: Combine eggs, corn syrup, salt, vanilla, sugar and butter. Mix well.
Add peanuts and stir.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 50 minutes longer.

title: creamy chicken 'n broccoli
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions; stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spread over bottom of 9-inch casserole dish.
Place broccoli atop stuffing.
Prepare cheese sauce mix according to package directions using 1 1/4 cups milk. Stir in sour cream.
Add chicken to cheese mixture.
Mix well and pour over broccoli.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add remaining onions and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: granny k's biscuits(made from mayonnaise)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the flour and the mayonnaise until flour is course.
Add milk slowly until the flour can be rolled into a dough.
You may not need all of the milk or you may have to add more.
Roll dough and cut out your biscuits.
Put the biscuits on a lightly greased pan and put them in the oven.
Cook until done.

title: cheesy pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook and stir beef over medium high heat until brown; drain.
Mix beef and remaining ingredients, except cheese, in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Break up tomatoes. Bake, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, 45 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.

title: hot sausage puffs
directions: Remove sausage from casings; cook meat in large skillet until no longer pink.
Drain fat; spoon sausage into large bowl and cool.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water; blend well.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on large cookie sheet, 2-inches apart, and bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Makes about 75 puffs.

title: fried pies
directions: Combine all ingredients (except filling). Mix with hands until dough no longer sticks to them. Roll into balls slightly larger than walnut. Roll out thin. Place spoonful of filling in center. Fold over and seal edge. (Dab with water and press firmly together.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; drain.
Saute in skillet onion, bell pepper, celery and margarine.
Combine tomato sauce, tomato juice, mushroom soup, mushrooms, pimento, garlic and broth; add to mixture in skillet.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together in a large baking dish.
Cover with foil. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Cook another 15 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 20 minutes in covered saucepan. Add potatoes and frozen vegetables.
Mix and cook 30 minutes in chicken broth mixture.
Add chicken soup and cheese.
Slowly cook until cheese is melted.
Can be frozen.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In 1 tablespoon of the bacon grease, saute onion until slightly brown.
Chop stems of mushrooms and add.
Cook until done.
Add sour cream, olives, bacon, basil, oregano and salt.
Cook the mushroom caps in a shallow microwaveproof dish for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High.
If necessary, dry up any moisture in the dish, then fill mushroom caps with mixture and cook on Medium-high or Roast for about 6 minutes for a high-powered microwave or more for a low-powered one.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into three 8 inch pans.
Bake for 25-30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Clean and flake salmon.
Add ingredients; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Dip in crumbs again; pan-fry in margarine or butter.

title: mrs. field's cookie recipe
directions: *Measure out 5 cups of oatmeal, then powderize.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese in mixer bowl; beat well.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Makes 15 servings.

title: apple salad
directions: Melt jello in hot water.
Add marshmallows.
Add cold water and let partially set.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Beat together 3/4 cup sugar, 2 eggs and juice of 1 lemon. Cook to full boil, stirring continuously.
Watch closely.
Let cool and add 3/4 container Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled jello and slice.
Great for Thanksgiving with turkey.

title: genuine southern fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with 2 teaspoons of salt.
Place on platter. Cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Pour 1-inch of oil into large, deep, heavy skillet.
Add butter and heat over medium-high heat at 375°.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in 1/2 cup water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix together all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls and brown slowly in oil.

title: "that egg thing"
directions: Combine the eggs, cheese, milk, dry mustard and salt and pepper.
Pour over bread; will be runny mixture.
Add sausage. Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes; uncover and brown 15 minutes.

title: play-doh
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Add food coloring.
Cook about 5 minutes to form a ball.
Let cool and then knead.

title: turkey burger
directions: In medium bowl, mix meat, horseradish, apple, onion, salt and parsley flakes.
Shape turkey mixture into four (1 inch) thick patties.
Spray rack in boiling pan with nonstick cooking spray. Place patties on rack.

title: cheese pineapple salad
directions: Mix
cheese,
pineapple
chunks
and
marshmallows in a large bowl
and
store
in
refrigerator.
Mix sugar and flour together; then add other ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler until mixture thickens.	Cool
and
pour
over top of cheese, pineapple and marshmallows.
The sauce will cover up to 8 cups of the cheese mixture.

title: drew's brownies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, margarine, sugar, milk, cocoa, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured oblong pan (9 x 13-inch) for about 45 minutes or until done.
Frost.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Crush saltine crackers; mix with crushed potato chips and bread crumbs.
Dredge chops with flour.
Mix egg and milk.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Melt butter in frying pan; brown both sides of chops.
Place in a pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 30 minutes, depending on thickness of chops.

title: dulce de leche(from argentina)
directions: Place unopened can of condensed milk in large saucepan.
Cover with water.
Place lid on saucepan.
Bring to a boil and continue to boil for 2 1/2 hours, being careful to replace water, as it evaporates.

title: cabbage with caraway
directions: Cook onion in shortening in skillet until golden.
Add cabbage and remaining ingredients except vinegar; cover.
Cook until just tender, about 20 minutes.
Add vinegar.

title: hot coleslaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Chop onion.
Shred carrot.
Mix cabbage, onion and carrot.
Add mayonnaise, salt and a lot of black pepper.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: me ma's tea cakes
directions: Cut
shortening
into
dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Knead into dough.
Roll out to desired thickness (very thin)
and cut in different shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
You
may	sprinkle
with	sugar
or sugar and cinnamon before you cut.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix cheese in while hot.
Beat with mixer.
Add other ingredients except pineapple and nuts with 7-Up last.
When slightly set, mix in nuts and pineapple.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together 2 eggs, slightly beaten, pumpkin, 1/3 cup sugar and spices.
Spread over bottom of pie shell.
Combine 2 eggs, corn syrup, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon over pumpkin.
Bake in oven for 50 minutes or until set.
Makes 1 pie.

title: lime bavarian salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello and salt into 2 cups boiling water.
Drain and reserve juice from crushed pineapple.
Combine reserved pineapple juice and enough water to make 2 cups.
Add to jello mixture; chill until slightly thickened.
Whip the cream.
Fold into jello with sugar and the drained pineapple.
Chill.
If desired, blend in nuts and cherries.

title: janice's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Season with red pepper to taste.
Garnish with paprika or nuts as desired.

title: mo-joes potatoes
directions: Slice raw potatoes with skins into 1/2-inch thick slices. Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Shake 'n Bake. Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put 1/2 stick margarine over the broccoli; add cheese.
Put in buttered casserole.
Crush the Ritz crackers with 1/2 stick margarine that has been melted.
Pat over top.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix all but last three ingredients together thoroughly and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut oleo into dry cake mix. Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with large Cool Whip and chopped nuts. Refrigerate.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Fill a large pot of water and blanch broccoli, cauliflower and red pepper 1 minute or until cooked to your liking.
Saute onions in oil.
Drain vegetables and toss with onions and hot fettucine. Top with parsley, salt, pepper and cheese.

title: hodge podge
directions: Brown meats with onion, drain if necessary.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer on low for two hours or cook on low setting in the crock pot for four hours.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate roast in refrigerator for 2 days.
Cook over low heat in covered pan until tender.

title: soy chicken skillet(low-fat)
directions: Cut chicken into strips and coat with flour.
In a large skillet, heat oil and brown the chicken.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Combine 1 cup of juice, soy, ketchup and honey.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
