Add celery, onion and garlic until tender.
Add broth, water, potatoes, carrots and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and simmer over medium heat until broth is slightly thickened; stir often.
Garnish with parsley before serving.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth. Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat in flour and salt. Stir in 1/2 of the chocolate chips.
Spread in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Immediately sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips and spread when melted.

title: microwave cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Prepare white sauce by melting the margarine over low heat. Stir in the flour. Gradually add the milk and cook, stirring until sauce thickens. Add the salt and cheese.
Stir until melted and brown. Alternately layer potatoes and sauce in 2-quart casserole dish forming 3 layers.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at Medium heat for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to oil mixture.
Add prunes, juice and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a large flat pan or two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs, salt and vanilla well.
Then add flour, cocoa and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and cover with marshmallows.
Bake for 5 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool.

title: grandmother clark fried steak
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steak portions; brown fairly quick in hot salad oil.
Blot excess salad oil and place in tightly covered roaster (or Dutch oven).
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 275°.
This will be a very moist steak.
(Spray pan with Pam.)
Can serve with cream gravy.

title: bologna and relish sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on white bread.
Top with a slice of olive.

title: so easy crock-pot spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet. Drain. Transfer to greased slow cooker. Add remaining ingredients, except dry spaghetti. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 3 1/2 hours. During last hour, turn to high and add dry spaghetti. Stir frequently to keep spaghetti from clumping together. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and frozen strawberries.
Place in freezer container.
Finish filling with milk and pop.
This makes 1 1/2 gallon but can be adopted to 1 gallon with less milk and pop.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Brown ground beef in large, deep frying pan.
Drain excess fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding with rum sauce
directions: Break the old bread into small pieces; place in bottom of oblong Pyrex dish.
In blender, mix together the sugar, eggs, milk, butter, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Blend well and pour over bread slowly so that bread will soak up mixture.
(Use potato masher and mix well for smooth pudding.)
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix
first
ingredients;
cool
to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in	1/4
cup
lukewarm
water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and stir into first mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups flour and mix thoroughly.
Then stir in the other 3 1/2 cups. Do not knead.

title: graham pralines
directions: Separate each graham cracker into four sections.
Line cookie sheet with crackers with edges touching.
Melt margarine in pan; stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes stirring frequently.
Spread over crackers evenly.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove and let cool on wax paper.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: Crumble half of cake in bowl.
Spread half of strawberries over cake.
Cover with half of glaze.
Spread half of pudding mixture over glaze.
Repeat with rest of ingredients.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: taco salad
directions: Boil meat in water; drain.
Return to saucepan and add fajita seasoning, kidney beans and picante sauce.
Mix well and let simmer as you prepare lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and green onions. Mix together with black olives and meat mixture.
Add crushed Doritos to mixture when ready to eat, or each person add his own.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Use a large, heavy saucepan.
Melt sugar and syrup over low heat.
Add raw peanuts.
Cook slowly; stir almost constantly until peanuts are golden.
Remove from heat and add soda and salt.
Stir only until soda is stirred through.
Pour onto greased cookie sheets.
(Don't touch after you pour it on the cookie sheets!) When candy is brittle, break up into chunks.

title: fruit slaw
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
In a small bowl, combine the reserved syrup, yogurt and lemon juice.
In a large bowl, combine the pineapple, cabbage, oranges, celery, nuts and raisins.
Fold in yogurt mixture.
Gently fold in the banana. Cover and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheesy beef n' mac bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a
10-inch skillet, cook beef and onion until beef is brown and onion is tender. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water, pepper, macaroni and 1/2 of the cheese.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with remaining cheese. Bake 25 minutes until hot and bubbling.

title: pistachio salad #1
directions: Mix
pineapple and pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip;
blend. Add nuts, if desired and mix well.

title: kringle's cut outs
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl on medium speed until well blended.
Beat in egg.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry mix into creamed mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
After refrigerating, heat oven to 375°.
Roll half of the dough out to about 1/8-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar or leave plain to frost when cooled.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 3 dozen (depending on size and shapes).

title: cheeseburger
directions: Combine egg, 1/3 cup of soup, crumbs, pickles, onions, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Fold in cherry pie filling; pour into an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Whip cream cheese and fold in Cool Whip; add crushed pineapple.
Blend well.
Spread over jelled cherry mix.
Cut into squares to serve, after topping is firm.

title: velvet shrimp
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Stir in green onions and 2 tablespoons seasoning mix; cook one minute.
Add shrimp and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes.
Stir in cream and remaining seasoning mix; cook 1 minute.
Remove shrimp with slotted spoon.
Boil cream in same skillet, whisking constantly, 2 minutes.
Stir in cheese, then shrimp.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: lucille's caramel cinnamon rolls
directions: Let bread dough rise until about double in bulk. Roll out to 1/2 inch. Spread butter all over. Combine 1 cup each brown and white sugar and cinnamon to taste. Sprinkle over butter. Roll dough as tight as possible, pinch seam together. Cut with very sharp knife 1 1/2 inch thick. Combine cream and 1 1/2 cups brown sugar and pour in 9 x 13 inch pan, then lay rolls on top. Let rise a little and bake at 350 about 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine bread crumbs and water.
Let soak for 5 minutes.
Peel onion.
Grate finely.
In another bowl, combine meat, grated onion, salt and pepper.
Add crumb mixture.
Combine until well blended.
Roll meat mixture into even meatballs with hands.

title: chicken brown rice primavera
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook and stir until chicken is lightly browned.
Add broth, broccoli, red pepper, carrots, squash and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: steamed carrots
directions: Wash, scrape and slice carrots in round disc shape.
Place a 2 to 3-quart size steamer basket in bottom of large cook pot.
Put enough water in pot so it does not rise above the steamer.
Add carrots to steamer.
Cover.
Cook on high heat for 5 minutes, then turn to low or simmer.
Carrots are done when tender to touch with fork.
Cooking time is about 15 to 20 minutes.
Check often.
When done, drain and place in serving dish.
Add butter to taste.
Stir and serve.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix together all ingredients but the corn.
Stir in the corn and then deep fry.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the sour cream, chillies, olives, onion and cheese.
Add chicken to mixture.
Dip tortillas in enchilada sauce one by one, then put 1/4 cup mix in tortilla.
Roll up and place in greased pan.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over rolled up tortillas and spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 enchiladas.

title: mexican bananas
directions: Remove skin from bananas; save skin.
Dip bananas in lemon juice.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Replace bananas in skins.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until skin is black.
Serve.

title: okra patties
directions: Drain okra; mash well.
Add egg and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to okra and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into very hot oil.
Fry until golden, turning once.

title: cheesy burger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. In a large skillet, brown beef and onion. Drain off all fat from beef. Stir in mustard, salt, garlic powder and pepper. Spoon 1/2 of beef mixture evenly into crust-lined pan. Top with cheese cubes. Add remaining beef. Spread evenly and drizzle with ketchup. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese. Top with second crust. Seal edges and flute. Cut holes in top crust. Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown. Serves 8.

title: b~b~q bean salad
directions: Cook pinto beans as directed.
Mix beans with pepper, onion and corn.

title: oreo pie
directions: Fold in
cookies and pour into chocolate graham cracker crust. Freeze.

title: joanne's blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine, let cool.
Then add to brown sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients, then add vanilla and nuts. Spread in well buttered 8-inch square pan and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, season meat with salt and pepper.
In separate bowl, soak bread in milk.
Mix meat with onion, then add bread and egg.
Roll into small 1-inch balls and place on broiler pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry and lemon cream mold
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in half of the boiling water; add half of the cold water and refrigerate.
Before the lemon gelatin sets, add whipping cream and sliced strawberries.
Dissolve the strawberry gelatin in the rest of the boiling water and add rest of the cold water.
When the lemon gelatin has set in mold, add strawberry gelatin.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with sugared strawberries and grapes or rosettes of whipped cream.

title: melissa's fairy biscuits
directions: Pour water over shortening.
Stir until melted and cool.
Drop in eggs, yeast and sugar; beat with egg beater.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Let rise about 2 hours.
Roll out and cut like biscuits.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add first 7 ingredients into saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Pour into pie shell; chill.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch rectangle baking dish; add all ingredients.
Stir slightly.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: irish soda bread(from grandma bridget higgins)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, buttermilk and Crisco oil. Set aside.
In a very large bowl, mix dry ingredients and raisins. Pour in buttermilk mixture and stir with wooden spoon.
As mixture gets thick, use bare hands to be sure all ingredients are mixed together well. Equally divide mixture into 3 well buttered bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Insert clean toothpick to test for doneness.
If particles cling to toothpick, bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
Wonderful to serve anytime.

title: nonfat lasagne
directions: Prepare overnight.
Use uncooked lasagne noodles (refrigerate overnight).
Spray Pam on pan.
Cover pan with layer of sauce, then arrange lasagne noodles.
Cover with sauce.
Add cheeses; repeat once or twice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: uncooked fudge
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix in sugar and water and beat in egg.
Add butter, one tablespoon at a time, beating well.
Stir in peanut butter gradually.
Pour into peanut oiled square pan and let set.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Mix until all dry ingredients are wet.
Line muffin tins (for as many muffins that you want).
Half fill with batter.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Break cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp then cut up into pieces, mix all together and add onion finely diced.
Add 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger and seasonings.
Combine with sauce.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sauce to cover, then noodles, then cheese.
Olives are on last layer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion.
Top with mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: broiled shrimp
directions: Simmer shrimp in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Permit to cool in water in which they have been cooked.
Dry them between towels. Chill them.
Serve them very cold in their shells (to be shelled at the table) with a bowl of your favorite dressing.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Wipe chicken breasts well with damp paper towels. In large bowl, combine sour cream with lemon juice, Worcestershire, celery salt, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper. Add chicken to sour cream mixture, coating each piece well. Let stand, covered, in the refrigerator overnight.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers. Stir to coat.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: foil pot roast
directions: Place meat on 30 x 18-inch piece of heavy-duty foil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place meat on foil.
Sprinkle dry soup over top of meat.
Spread mushroom soup over dry topping.
Fold foil over meat, sealing securely.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients,
except
pecans thoroughly; fold in pecans.
Pour into cookie
shell and top with meringue, whipped cream or other whipped topping.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Stir	in all dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add	oil, eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrots in large bowl.
In another bowl, combine ingredients and add to cabbage mixture and toss well. Yields 8 (1/2 cup) servings.
Contains 30 calories each serving.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Grease pan. Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened. Beat vigorously 1 minute. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Makes 1 large loaf.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Add mayonnaise, eggs and cheese.
Mix well.
Put into casserole dish. Add mushroom soup and spread over top.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Mix with crackers (crushed) and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry champagne
directions: Combine strawberries and lemonade in container of an electric blender.
Top with cover and process until smooth and thickened. To serve, combine strawberry mixture and champagne in a large pitcher or punch bowl.
Stir well.
Serve immediately.
Yields 7 1/2 cups.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Spread half of stuffing mix with margarine in bottom of dish. Spread cabbage and onion over crumbs.
Mix milk, soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage-onion layer.
Spread cheese over soup.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.
Microwave remaining 2 ounces almond bark and oil in 1 cup measure for 1 minute.
Stir.
Continue microwaving until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into wedges.
Makes a nice Christmas treat!

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake mix for 5 minutes less than directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cream margarine, eggs, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Beat until creamy and spread over cooled cake.
Seal edges.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Set aside 1/2 cup broth from chicken.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Combine soups, milk and 1/2 cup reserved broth in pan.
Cook until heated through, stirring well.
Combine stuffing mix and melted oleo. Spread half in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top of stuffing; pour soup over chicken and top with remainder of stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cloud salad
directions: Blend and chill. Good salad for a luncheon. Delicious and quick.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes. Add soup, simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Heat.
Serve on toast or over rice.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Layer chicken, broccoli, bread crumbs (sprinkle seasoning from dressing mix over crumbs), cheese, soup and water chestnuts. Continue to layer until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: summer cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges for 4 minutes.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans for 20 minutes or 2 (9-inch) pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and ginger.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Preheat 1 tablespoon of oil in wok, uncovered, for 1 minute.
Add carrots.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add reserved mushroom liquid, cover and steam 4 minutes.
Remove carrots. Heat 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add cauliflower and pea pods.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add onion and mushrooms; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add meat; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Combine water, cornstarch and sugar.
Stir into mixture and cook until thickened.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans.
Cool. Split layers horizontally.
Melt the chips in saucepan over very low heat. Cool, then beat in margarine.
Add almonds. Spread one cake layer with 1/2 chocolate mixture. Top with second layer of cake and spread with 1/2 Cool Whip. Repeat layers. Garnish with shaved chocolate curls and almonds.
Chill 1 hour.

title: rich and simple french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in an 8-quart stockpot on medium heat.
Add olive oil and stir.
Add onions and continually stir until tender and translucent.
Do not brown the onions.
Add beef stock, sherry and thyme.

Season with salt and pepper and simmer for 30 minutes. Ladle soup into individual, oven-safe, serving bowls and place one slice of bread on top (it can also be broken into pieces, whichever you prefer).
Layer cheese on top of bread, placing a slice of Provolone, 1/2 slice diced Swiss and then Parmesan cheese.
Place bowls on cookie sheet and broil until cheese bubbles and browns slightly.

title: wooden shoe barbecue
directions: Fry ground beef; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Add ingredients to ground beef.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve on buns with cole slaw.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Slowly add milk, mix very well.
If still lumpy, let set about 5 minutes.
Then add lemon juice and vanilla.
Top with cherry pie filling, or whatever you prefer.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients together and shape into balls.
Brown and place in single layer pan.
In saucepan, mix last 4 ingredients for sauce and heat.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves a lot of people!

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil or spray with nonstick spray a large baking sheet.
Put kidney beans and oil in bowl and mash.
Sprinkle with cumin, chili powder and garlic powder; mix well.
Add chilies and mix again; divide mixture evenly and spread over 4 tortillas, staying 1-inch away from edges of tortilla.
Top each one with another tortilla.
Spread 1/4 cup salsa over top of each tortilla; sprinkle evenly with green pepper, onions and olives.
Divide cheese evenly and sprinkle over top.
Bake 15 minutes and serve.
Serves 4.

title: yams hawaiian style
directions: Slice yams into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Combine pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in 2-quart casserole.
Place in microwave oven and cook 4 minutes; stir.
Sprinkle top with pecans and brown sugar.
Continue cooking 2 to 4 minutes until topping has melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well (use hands if necessary).
Put into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Leftovers make great sandwiches.

title: ice cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the cold water and set aside. Scald milk. Add gelatin mixture, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
Let cool. Add beaten eggs, canned milk and vanilla.
(I don't add all of the 7 cups of milk until I get it in the freezer container.)
Add milk, but leave 1 1/2 to 2-inches space at top of can as it is fuller after it is frozen.
This makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: In saucepan, mix together the water, sugar, syrup and cornstarch.
Boil until clear.
Add 1/2 package gelatin.
Cook until just warm.
Add peaches.
Pour into pie shell; top with topping.

title: liver roll-ups(appetizers)
directions: Fold 1/3 of a chestnut in each liver and wrap with bacon. Secure with toothpick.
Marinate at least 4 hours in soy sauce. Dip each one in brown sugar.
Boil about 15 minutes until liver is done.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes and onion in greased 2-quart casserole until all ingredients are used.
Blend rest of ingredients in bowl.
Pour over potatoes.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lazy lady banana pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas and pour mixture over.
Let chill at least an hour.
Keep in refrigerator.
I always double the recipe.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Bake skinned chicken at 350° for 1 hour; cool.
Debone and break into pieces.
While chicken is cooking, chop veggies.
In large pot, saute peppers, onions, garlic and zucchini for several minutes in olive oil.
Add mushrooms during last minute.
Add sauce, paste, wine, sugar, chicken and spices.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Boil pasta of your choice; drain well.
Melt in 1/4 stick of butter.
Top with sauce and grated cheese.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Tear lettuce.
Add beef, cheese, onion and tomatoes.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on top.
Mix.
Pour whole bottle of dressing over all ingredients; mix well.
Break up some Doritos, leave some whole.
Mix into salad before serving.
Save some chips to garnish.

title: pumpkin chip cake
directions: Mix by hand in mixing bowl, then add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour in a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: punch
directions: Boil
sugar
in
small amount of water until dissolved. Add a few drops of red (or other color) food coloring.
Finish filling gallon with water.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Barbecue or broil chicken with teriyaki sauce.
Shred lettuce and cabbage; add chopped green onions.
Toast sesame seed and almonds; add to salad.
Top with Top Ramen noodles, chow mein noodles, Chinese white noodles or wontons (sliced thin and deep fried).

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg yolks, milk and flour (with soda and baking powder).
Mix well and add coconut extract.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 350° oven until done. Let stand for 10 minutes, then turn out on cooling racks.
Use coconut milk with 1 cup sugar, boiled together.
Add coconut and cool slightly; spread between layers.
Spread with Divinity Icing, top and sides.
Better made 2 days before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomatoes, beans, onion, pepper and taco seasoning.
Cook until onion is tender.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix Mexican cornbread (by directions) and spread on top.
Cook at 450° until cornbread is done.

title: simple chocolate icing
directions: Use canned milk to mix to consistency with a mixer.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and chop.
Save broth.
Layer chicken, onion and cheese.
Heat soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and 1 cup broth. Pour over casserole.
Add Doritos on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Drain.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar and let cool.
Add onion, celery, pickle relish and eggs.
Set aside.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla on high until thick and lemon colored, about 4 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat on low just until combined.
Heat milk and butter in a small saucepan, until butter melts.
Add to butter and beat thoroughly.
(The batter is thin.)
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until cake is done.
Cool lightly.

title: delicious dilly dip
directions: Fold the above ingredients together.
For maximum flavor, let stand overnight in refrigerator. Can be used for dip with vegetables, potato chips, thin cut pumpernickel bread, or as topping on baked potatoes.

title: brussels sprouts and peas in brown butter
directions: Trim off stem and any yellow leaves from Brussels sprouts. Slice sprouts vertically into 1/4-inch thick slices.
From lemon, grate 1 teaspoon peel and squeeze 1 tablespoon juice.
In 12-inch skillet melt butter over medium-high heat and cook 2 minutes or until light golden brown, stirring.
Add sliced Brussels sprouts and stir to coat with browned butter.
Add 1/4 cup water and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and add lemon peel, peas, salt, pepper and another 1/4 cup water.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally and stir in juice.
Serves 8.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes; spread in pie shell.
Toss cheese with flour; sprinkle over mushrooms and onions.
Beat eggs with remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: beef mushroom stew
directions: Place in casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 3 hours. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: microwave harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a 1-quart glass casserole.
Stir in vinegar and reserved beet liquid.
Cook in microwave oven 3 to 4 minutes at High or until mixture boils and thickens slightly; stir twice.
Add beets and butter to thickened sauce; stir.
Cook in microwave oven 2 to 3 minutes at High or until thoroughly heated; stir once.
Makes 4 servings.
Can also be made on stovetop.

title: black walnut dover cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and butter.
Add baking soda and cream of tartar to flour.
Add flour mixture, beginning with flour, adding milk and ending with flour.
Add black walnuts.
Coat walnuts with part of the flour.
Pour in a well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: white trash
directions: Melt chocolate, margarine and peanut butter on low burner. Pour this mixture over the first 5 ingredients.
Then put all of this into a large plastic bag.
Then add powdered sugar to the mixture and shake well.
This is great for Christmas or Christmas gifts.

title: linda smith's ranch beans
directions: Saute onions and peppers.
Fry bacon and hamburger.
Drain beans.
Add the remaining ingredients in a buttered 13 x 9-inch dish or pan.
Stir in tomato soup and top with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: deviled potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with salt; drain. Add butter and warm milk; mash well. Heat 1/2 cup sour cream; add a little mustard (dry or prepared) and 2 tablespoons chopped green onions and a good big pinch of brown sugar. Stir all into potato mixture. Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fancy baked potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes lengthwise.
Soak for about 30 minutes in cold water.
Then drain.
Melt butter in a baking dish. Shake potatoes in flour mixture (flour, cheese and salt), using a paper or plastic bag.
Put potatoes in a greased baking dish and bake, turning once.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are browned.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place them in an ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients in medium bowl and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until blended.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: german chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk over low heat, stirring until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese and add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture and pour into crust.
Freeze about 4 hours.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chops.
Brown chops on each side in oil.
Use a cast-iron skillet if possible.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Sprinkle rice around chops.
Cover with a tight lid and cook 1 hour on low heat.
Check occasionally to see that the heat is not too high.
You may have to add a little water if it gets too dry.

title: basic applesauce
directions: Wash, core, pare and slice apples.
Add water and cook over medium heat until apples are tender.

title: mild salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in large kettle. Cook over low heat, simmering for 1 hour. Fill clean, hot pint or quart jars and cover with 2 piece lids. Place in hot water bath for 20 minutes. Yield: 7 quarts or 14 pints.

title: nutty rice
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Press this into 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Add to this the can of beef consomme and beef bouillon.
With one of the empty cans, add 1 can of water, 1 cup rice, salt, pepper and 1 package of slivered almonds.
Stir mixture together.
Bake in a covered dish for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8.

title: chicken bake
directions: You also need a flat pan, buttered.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Bring soup to boil.
Add gelatin and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased mold.
Chill until firm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco sauce.
Keep hot on stove.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onions; mix all together with cheese and Doritos.
When ready to serve, add hot mixture and toss, then serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with bread crumbs.
Brown sausage; drain and spread over bread.
Beat eggs.
Add soup, milk and seasoning.
Mix and pour over sausage.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat milk and egg.
Blend dry ingredients and gradually add milk mixture, beating constantly until batter is smooth.
Heat deep fat to 375°.
Holding your finger over bottom of a funnel, having a 3/8-inch to 1/2-inch hole, fill funnel with batter.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: boneless hilton head chicken
directions: Place chicken in large baking dish.
Place a slice of cheese on each chicken breast.
Mix soup and wine and pour over chicken. Spread sliced mushrooms over all.
Top with dry stuffing mix. Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: crunchy potato balls
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients and mix well.
Add enough flour to make it stiff.
Chill and then shape into balls and roll in corn flakes.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake for 25-30 minutes at 350 degrees. Serve hot.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend together and frost.
Good to use on pumpkin bars.

title: pizza pronto
directions: Place the pizza crust on a baking sheet.
Combine tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic powder; spread over crust. Top with cheese, pepperoni and olives.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until bubbling and heated through.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and whip.
Serve over seafood.

title: scratch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a sheet cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt; add shortening and bananas.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and beat two minutes on medium.
Turn into pans and bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool ten minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pans.
Frost with cream cheese frosting and garnish with finely chopped walnuts.

title: queen muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients until moist.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.
You can add 1 cup apples, if you like.

title: apple surprise
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.
If mixture is too thick add some of
the
pineapple juice until desired consistency is obtained.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese in blender.
Stir in zest and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
If a thinner consistency is desired, add a little orange juice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large mixer bowl; mix well. Add flour, baking soda and salt gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread and coconut in sweet milk.
Add evaporated milk. Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar and beat until slightly thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.
Mix well; then stir in bread mixture.
Stir well.
Add raisins.
Let set for 3 to 5 minutes; pour into dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Put well mixed ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 box of dry yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Drizzle 1 cup melted oleo on cake mix.
Sprinkle 1 cup nut meats on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with corn chips.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute bacon until crispy and chop into bits.
Reserve.
Saute chopped onion in a few tablespoons of bacon grease.
Prepare enough rice mixture to yield 1 1/2 cups cooked rice.
Prepare the cream of potato soup with the milk and/or half and half.
Combine soup, rice and cheese.
Heat gently until cheese melts.
Garnish with bacon bits.

title: barbecue pork ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over meat.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel jumbo potatoes and dice into small pieces about the size of the end of your finger until you have 5 measuring cups of raw potatoes.
After cooking, you will end up with about 4 cups.
Save liquid in pot.
Place potatoes in oven-safe dish, adding white sugar between layers.
Top with brown sugar, a sprinkling of cinnamon (as desired) and margarine.
Pour liquid from pot on top of potatoes until they are barely covered.
Place in oven and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets; cool and remove jackets.
Cut up and keep warm.
In iron skillet, fry bacon crisp.
Take bacon from pan and add to potatoes.
Add flour to 1/2 hot drippings and brown, stirring constantly.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook to a thin gravy and pour over potatoes.
Stir in raw onions.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown together meat and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Add 2 cups water and thicken mixture with flour.
Add corn.
Put mixture in greased casserole dish.
Spread about 2 inches of mashed potatoes on top.
Dot with oleo and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sylvia's chop suey
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and simmer for hours.
Just before serving, mix together cornstarch and water.
Mix into chop suey and stir until liquid has cleared.
Serve over white rice.

title: almond mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems and reserve.
Pat mushroom caps dry and sprinkle inside of caps with Accent.
Chop mushroom stems very fine.
Combine with bread crumbs, lemon juice, rosemary, marjoram, salt, almonds and capers. Spoon mixture into caps and dot each mushroom with butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately. Serves 1 1/2 dozen.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies (set aside about 1 cup to use later).
Put crushed cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour melted butter over them.
Mix well and press down to make crust.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add marshmallow cream.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.
Serve with chunks of cantaloupe, honeydew melon, pineapple, apple, banana, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: vinegar dressing for banana salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cook until reasonably thick.
Cool. Pour over sliced bananas and add peanuts.
